animal.description:
Welcome Sam! 
Sam is back with the rescue after he was severely stressed in the home who adopted him a few years ago. 
He was running after the delivery guys.
He is a typical chihuahua as he wants things his way! Lol
He wants a calm and loving household. He’d love to be the only dog, but is fine with smaller dogs, big dogs he’s kind of intimidated by! 
No young kids, like I said he gets stressed out. 
He’s about 2 years old. Fully vetted, and neutered and microchipped! 
He’s good on a leash, loves car rides, and loves sleeping in bed with his human! 
If interested in this little guy, please fill out an application at danteshope.com

animal.description:
We are always looking for fosters. If you are curious on how you can be one please contact rescueme93@yahoo.com for more information.

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Harley and Casey

Our two new superstars. 15 y/o Pom/Poo brothers who are looking for a new home because their mom could no longer care for them. These brothers are a joy. 

The smaller one (Harley is active, lively and loves attention. Casey the bigger one is more quiet android back. Both boys have Cushings which is being treated with medication. We will be getting a dental on both boys ASAP. 

These guys will bring a lot of life and love into a quieter home. If you are interested in these guys (they must go together) 

Both online and pdf applications are available online at
http://members.petfinder.com/~MI730/ . The pdf can be printed, scanned and emailed to rescueme93@yahoo.com .
(Copy and Paste http://members.petfinder.com/~MI730/ into browser).

PetSmart is resuming on site adoptions on Saturdays with a limited number of animals. Personal meet and greets will continue to be scheduled offsite with an approved app. only.

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Both online and PDF application are available online at http://members.petfinder.com/~MI730/ under the links section on the left.

We show most of our adoptable pets at PetSmart, Utica, each Saturday from 11 to 3. If you are interested in a particular pet, we suggest you email: rescueme93@yahoo.com to see if that pet will be there.

Applications are approved on the basis of the best and most appropriate home for the animal, not on a first come, first served basis. On site adoption available to pre-approved applicants only.

Adoption Fees 
Senior 		: 9 years & up $100-$175 
Adult  		: 2 years to 8 years  $250
Young adult	: 6 months to 2 years $275 
Puppies		: 6 weeks to 6 months $300

Adoption fees go towards vaccines, heartworm prevention/testing, flea/tick prevention, spay/neuter and other medical problems that may arise.

MMAR is an all volunteer, foster based, 501 (c) 3, non profit organization. Without your donation, wonderful pets like these have to be passed by because we cannot afford their care.

If you would like to donate please send donation to: MMAR Box 180155 Utica, MI 48318

Donate online at http://members.petfinder.com/~MI730/  .

Please email us at rescueme93@yahoo.com for additional information or to set up special appointments.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.wagoninn.rescuegroups.org

Luna is a beautiful white pup who looks to be a mix of shepherd or husky and/or akita. Luna is a bit of a special girl as she was on the run in Louisiana for 4 months until she was finally trapped by animal control. She is now in a loving foster home in Louisiana learning the joy and comfort of being an inside dog. Luna is coming to NJ February 6th and needs a special home to keep her safe and teach her love. Luna is a flight risk and will required an experienced adopter who will take the proper precautions for her.

Luna is dog friendly! She seems to be afraid of the outdoor cats around her Louisiana foster home. She has been fixed, microchipped and she is up to date on vaccines. Luna is heartworm negative. Her adoption fee is $400.

How to Adopt Me!

If you are interested in learning more about me, and possibly making me part of your family, please go to wagoninn.rescuegroups.org. Click on the orange Online Adoption Application button to fill out an application. A Wag On Inn volunteer will be in touch soon!

animal.description:
{s3829code380/}
If you would like to provide this dog a loving home, please fill out a pre-adoption application.

Have a question? Please read our Frequently Asked Questions and Adoption Processed Explained documentation.
_________ B I O ______________

Name:Diamond
Size: ~Medium range: 26-60 lbs
Adoption Donation:$250 (applicable sales tax included).Adoption fees may be paid by cash or check.
Other:Spayed Female, Vaccinations current, Microchip, Dog-savvy cats only

Diamondis looking for that special place just for her...is it with you?

Foster Home Feedback

*
Diamond has been diagnosed with Dynamic Right Ventricular Outflow Tract Obstruction. This means the right side of her heart collapses when it pumps causing a swishing sound resulting in a grade 2 heart murmur. This is a mild heart condition but does require she be on Enalapril 10mg once a day, the cost of this medication is $25 per month. Diamond also has food sensitivities and requires a special diet. She is on Royal Canin Hydrolyzed Protein Diet. The cost of this food is about $97.00 for a 25-pound bag. ~ Diamond also experiences intermittent bouts of vomiting/urping, and she is on Metoclopramide to help prevent this and treat /nauseousness. The cost of this medication is $19 per month

1/27/21: Diamond is a very special dog who - like most dogs - won't be perfect for every family, but for that special family she will be an irreplaceable and beyond perfect addition.

Diamond came to us very very scared of life and unbeknownst to any in the rescue, very sick. Over the past 5 months as our foster, she has become the best version of her healthy self and is working on adjusting to life as a house pet.

She is the most stoic and non-reactive dog we have ever had as our foster. Diamond is very good with all dogs she has met and has become a polite housemate to our cat (she was a little too interested in our cat for the first few weeks but with time learned that our cat is basically "one of the dogs". I feel Diamond would do ok in a home with cats who are dog-savvy. She has learned to like playing with our dogs on occasion but for the most part, loves to just curl up in one of the many dog beds we have laying around the house and snooze the day away in a peaceful home.

Diamond kennels beautifully and I've honestly only heard her bark a few times in the past 5 months as our foster. And each time it was just a single bark because she was upset about something, like not being picked first for going on a walk. Diamond walks great with her harness and passes dogs and people she sees like a champ. Although she's a little too timid to initiate meeting people, she is always polite.

Diamond prefers a peaceful and quiet home, so I feel a home with children would not be her ideal fit. She would love a small family, with maybe a doggy playmate to show her the world isn't so scary, and most importantly someone to love her and give her the time she needs to adjust and learn that life isn't something to be scared of.

Everyone who has ever met Diamond has instantly fallen in love with her soulful eyes and gentle being. She is one of the most memorable and amazing fosters we have ever had (and we've had many!). I encourage you to fill out an application if you feel you are her forever family.Click here to watch a video of Diamond.To view additional dogs available for adoption, please see our website: www.4luvofdog.org

animal.description: I'm just so pleased to meet you! My name is Coco. I'm a 4 year old happy-go-lucky pupper who is on the market for a new best friend! animal.description:
Fern is on hold until she can be spayed, but you can submit applications if interested. she is being fostered in NJ.

What Fern's foster mom has to say about Fern:
Fern spent two full days on transport to get to us for fostering. All of the drivers fell in love with her! Fern is still losing her pregnancy weight - she gave birth to 5 puppies in November. As soon as her mammary glands shrink more, she will be able to be spayed.
Fern is either all out sleeping and cuddling or all out playing. She greets us with full-body wags in the mornings and when we come home. Fern loves belly rubs! She enjoys walks and does very well on a leash. She also loves to lie in the sun in the backyard. She plays with plush toys and chews hard bones. Fern loves to play “tag” in the yard. She runs around and then stops. I have to tag her and then she’ll start running again. She is so much fun!
Fern is not food aggressive and is very gentle taking treats. She can be very lazy, sleeping in any empty space - couch, bed, table, etc. And she’s quite stubborn if you try to get her to move before she’s ready!
Fern quickly learned her way around our small home. She knows where to find the water bowl, and she will go to the back door and bark when she needs to go out. She will whine a little bit if she can’t find you - and then comes right to you when you call her name.
I can’t imagine any family where Fern would not be a good fit. She is so perfect and will be a joy to the family who adopts her!
BDRA has voted against the use of electrical fencing effective immediately.

animal.description:
With the looks that rival those of Justin Timberlake or Justin Bieber, depending on your generation, this young Rottweiler mix will be turning heads on walks around the neighborhood! About 2 years old, Justin is a long and lean 54 lbs with some filling out to do. He's an energetic and athletic guy who is having a blast playing with his doggy pals on the farm and has never met a person he didn't like. He may do best with older kids, as he is still in need of some more formal training and not fully aware of his size, but is eager to learn and eager to please. We've quickly fallen head over heels for his handsome boy and we are sure you will too! Be sure to hurry and submit your adoption request to meet Justin, because this chart-topper surely won't be on the farm long!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

She gets along with other dogs and would be fine with cats and kids as well, but she does have a grumpy streak when you approach her if she is already in a lap and for this reason we urge caution if you have children in your home. Angel is another senior who deserves a happy life and has years of love to give!

animal.description:
Exuberant, play driven, and headstrong, Buck has endless energy. Buck is always on the go, and is looking for someone to match his outgoing personality and high scale spirit.

As well as high energy, Buck also has high anxiety; especially in relation to being alone. Buck would like nothing more in the world then to find a human to be with all of the time (he is what some would call a stage-5 clinger). If you are in reach, he is the happiest of boys!

Some of Bucks favorite activities are playing fetch, going for walks, mental stimulation games, car rides, and more fetch. While Buck has good leash manners, he does walk with a purpose and generally is a stride ahead of you. He can be reactive when first meeting other dogs, and becomes a strong puller when passing others out in the world.

In regards to meeting other dogs in general, Buck has a very large bark which can be off-putting to new dogs (and some people). With positive redirection he quiets himself down, and with time he can learn to be friends with dogs of his size. He is not suggested to be with small dogs or cats. 

Bucks ideal home would be with an experienced and active owner, who is home majority of the time and can work with his separation anxiety. Due to his ample energy and uncoordinated body/mouth, he is not suited for a home with small children. He would also benefit from a large yard with lots of space to run and play.

Buck came into care with bladder stones, and is required to be on a prescription urinary diet to keep them from reoccurring. This will be a life long diet.

We anticipate a large number of inquiries for Buck. We ask for patience in waiting for a response, as we will be working diligently to find the best match for him and only reaching out to successful candidates. Primary Color: Black Secondary Color: Tan Weight: 40kg Age: 2yrs 0mths 3wks Animal has been Neutered

animal.description:
Kylie is a very pretty 2 ½ -to- 3 year old pup who looks like a Rhodesian Ridgeback/ Hound Dog/ maybe Labrador blend.  I just can’t quite figure her out, but she’s a lovely, sweet, amusing girl.

An on-line “DNA test” – based more on appearances than actual DNA – shows her to be 73% Rhodesian Ridgeback.

Kylie is medium sized – she weighs maybe 40 – 45 pounds full grown.

She’s also very smart, and I am particularly partial to smart dogs, and Kylie fits the bill to a “T.”

Kylie is very sweet and tolerant.  When I first fostered her, she seemed afraid of men, but now she gets along well with both men and women.  She would probably be best with teenagers, instead of little kids, just because she is rather active.

She comes when she is called and gets along great with my other foster dogs. Although she is a big strong hound, she doesn’t need to be the dominant dog and fits right in the middle of the group. 

Kylie never wanders or digs in the yard. In fact, when she is in the front yard (which isn’t fenced), she just hangs out and is wonderful well-behaved. She is just a happy-go-lucky girl.

She is good-natured and smart, but she could use some basic training. 

I think Kylie would make a perfect family buddy for a very active family – she is loving, a great size, active, and fun to be with.

Kylie is quiet, so she won’t disturb your neighbors at all.

Kylie is completely house trained and crate trained.

Although she is wonderfully gentle and tolerant, a girl like Kylie will keep you and your children safe.  

In fact, Kylie is the sort of pup you can walk or hike with late at night in a secluded area and feel safe – not because she is the tiniest bit mean or nasty, but because she just looks protective!

At the moment, this funny girl is curled up on the cool floor beside my desk as I type this--she is such a mellow sweetheart.

There is something simply lovable about Kylie – maybe it is the warm expression on her face or maybe it is how her eyes look right into yours with love – she seems like a special rescue to me.

She is active, healthy, and young, but not at all hyper. She can play like a puppy, and she LOVES her toys!

Kylie has a lovely, sweet face, and big soft brown eyes.  

Of course, Kylie is spayed, up to date on all her shots, and ready for her forever home.

I am a firm believer in allowing people who are interested in adopting one of my rascals to have a sleepover (which can be more than one day), so you might want to take this big lug home to see how you, your family, your other pets, and Kylie all adapt to one another.  

To meet this great pupper and the rest of our other great foster doggies, please email crittersandrascals@gmail.com                                  (pls no calls or texts)

Lucky is a 6-month old blue pitty looking for a foster or adopt. Lots of puppy energy! His best home will be where he is the center of attention with no other pets in the home. 
The Adoption Process


	If you are ready to meet the pet, please fill out an online adoption application by copying and pasting the following link into your internet browser: https://www.petstablished.com/adoption_form/10666/generic
	Once your application is submitted, we will contact the vet reference provided. If you do not yet have a vet, please provide three personal references these could be family and friends who can attest to your pet parenting skills.
	A volunteer will schedule a phone interview with you. The interview and application help our fosters find their forever home by ensuring a good match. 
	The Louisa Humane Society does not have a brick and mortar facility, so all of our pets are in foster care. Once approved, the foster parent will reach out to arrange a visit. The foster family can tell you all about her likes, dislikes, and little quirks. 
	The application and visit do not oblige you to adopt, but if youre ready to take the pet home as your furry forever friend, the adoption fee is $300.


Should the match turn out less than perfect, or if you are unwilling or unable to care for an adopted animal, the Louisa Humane Society will take the animal back into our care.

animal.description:
Meet  Peppy  ~

My name is Peppy and I am a 6 year old Chihuahua from South Carolina.  I weigh roughly  7 lbs.

I am a very sweet guy for sure! I love being held or just sitting on a lap. Barking is not big on my priority list so I am pretty quiet. I am great in the crate and don't mind it a bit!
But big dogs beware! I may be small but I am not stupid! I will not hesitate to strike at you like a snake, if you come too close!

With my adorable looks, and unbridled loyalty, I will always be there for you through thick and thin. I will never judge you, or turn my back on you. Every single day, you will look at me and you will know that you are loved unconditionally. I will never betray you or hurt you, and I will grow old by your side.

******IMPORTANT - PLEASE READ ALL THE GREAT INFO BELOW******

***Please don't apply unless you are very serious about adopting, and are ready to move forward with the adoption process. We are super busy and make a great effort to respond back to EVERYONE ASAP! WHEN WE TAKE THE TIME TO PROCESS AN APPLICATION AND RESPOND BACK TO THE APPLICANT JUST TO BE EITHER IGNORED OR BE TOLD THEY CANNOT COME FOR SEVERAL DAYS, MORE TIME IS WASTED~PLEASE HAVE MORE RESPECT THAN THAT!

PLEASE read our website's ADOPTION PROCESS PAGE prior to submitting an adoption application. www.apupspizzazzrescue.com/adoption-process 
ADOPTION APPLICATION: www.apupspizzazzrescue.com/adoption-application 

ABOUT OUR RESCUE DOGS: 
 All of our dogs are located in Connecticut, are spayed or neutered, up to date on vaccines, microchipped, have been given deworming medications, and have had CT State health checks, & go home with a leash, collar, & packet of medical paperwork. 

BREED IDENTIFICATION:
Please understand that many rescue dogs are mixes of multiple breeds. Petfinder allows us to choose up to two breeds per dog. While the shelters and our rescue do our best in accurately identifying breeds, breed identification is not guaranteed. If there is a certain breed that you do not want, it is very important that you share this with our rescue when applying. When adopting a puppy, breed uncertainty plays a big part in the size/look of the dog as an adult. Please know that any puppy can be a wonderful dog, regardless of preconceived notions of certain breeds, but it is very important that the adopter has the dedication and patience to raise the puppy with boundaries, consistency, structure, & love. The more effort you give towards training & time you allow for exercise, your puppy will grow to be a HUGE source of UNCONDITIONAL LOVE, TOTAL LOYALTY, HAPPINESS, COMFORT & COMPANIONSHIP!

ABOUT OUR RESCUE:
We are a small rescue run by volunteers & focused on finding the right match for both our dogs & for you. If you are interested in adopting through our rescue, you first will need to complete an adoption application & be approved as a potential adopter before meeting any of our pups. No need to be intimidated by our application as it allows us to get to know you & your lifestyle. Of course, the more you can share the better! Please also note, while a fenced yard is fantastic, it is not required by our rescue, however, it may be required for a certain dog occasionally.  Once adoption applicants are approved to become potential adopters, we offer private appointments where you can meet one or several dogs at the discretion of the rescue. We offer a unique & pleasant experience focused on finding the perfect match. It is extremely important to us that everyone is treated with respect & that NO ONE IS LEFT HANGING. WE WILL GET BACK TO YOU WITHIN 2 TO 3 DAYS of application submission. If there is a dog you are eager to meet, please  TEXT US DIRECTLY at 203-241-2351 so that we can check the status of your application and move it forward immediately. We look forward to hearing from you and helping you find your new best friend.

*All adult dogs can be cat tested by request.

HOME/RENTER INSURANCE:
SOME PROVIDERS HAVE VERY STRICT POLICIES REGARDING WHICH TYPE OF DOG BREEDS ARE ALLOWED UNDER THEIR COVERAGE. STATE FARM WAS SUGGESTED TO US AS THEY DO NOT PUNISH, DROP, NOR REFUSE YOU DUE TO DOG BREED SHOULD YOU RUN INTO ISSUES WITH YOUR CURRENT PROVIDER.

animal.description:
[IF DOGS ARE POSTED THAT MEANS THEY ARE AVAILABLE! PLEASE DO NOT EMAIL ASKING IF THEY ARE AVAILABLE. IF THEY ARE POSTED, THEY ARE AVAILABLE — IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN SETTING UP A MEET AND GREET, SUBMIT AN APPLICATION THECANTUFOUNDATION.ORG ]

Hi! My name is Vicky! I am an 8 month, female, beagle mix weighing in at a about 20 pounds! I am here because the wonderful people at The Cantu Foundation found and saved me from the streets, they found me tied up! I am house trained and working on my leash manners and I’m ready to come home with you. I just know we can be best friends!
 
I am lovable, playful and curious and I love my toys! I am great with other dogs at my foster home and I’m good with kids and cats! I don’t want any fur siblings that are too small like bunnies or hamsters because I like to chase them. Once I get all my puppy energy out, I love naps and cuddling! I also love to watch out the window and see what’s happening out in the world from the house or the car. I’d love a new family that likes to be outside with me!
 
I hope to go to a new home with a family that is ready to grow with me and help train me to be a good doggie in the years to come. I can go to a home with dog and human siblings and love to be active! I love everyone so far and adjust well to my surroundings after a short time! My adoption fee is $500 and that includes spaying/neutering and vetting care. If you want to take me home, please fill out the form on the website here http://www.thecantufoundation.org/adopt.html

animal.description:
*Due to concerns surrounding COVID-19, we have reformatted the way that we do adoptions in order to follow social distancing protocols. We are thrilled that so many people want to adopt right now, but we are not equipped to handle the large number of calls, applications, and email inquiries we are receiving. We are no longer answering phone calls and are doing all communications with adopters via email. If you have a dog you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application before sending us emails. When your application has been processed, you will receive an email from us with further instructions on how to adopt. You do not need a new application for every dog that you are interested in adopting. 

At MAMCO we understand that in order to continue rescuing moms and babies, we must stretch our finances as far as we are able. For this reason we use variable adoption pricing. By assigning higher adoption fees to high demand moms and puppies, we are able to rescue more families in need.The money raised through these adoptions acts as a benefactor to moms and puppies in our care who require expensive veterinary treatments, have behavioral issues, or need more time to find a home. We often reduce the adoption fees on these harder-to-place moms and puppies to help them find forever families. Adoption fees vary, but all include spay or neuter, microchip, up to date vaccinations and deworming, rabies vaccine at the time of spay or neuter, and 30 days of pet insurance. We also cover hernia repair and cherry eye repair at the time of spay or neuter. Applications can be filled out at mamcorescue.org.

animal.description:
*Due to concerns surrounding COVID-19, we have reformatted the way that we do adoptions in order to follow social distancing protocols. We are thrilled that so many people want to adopt right now, but we are not equipped to handle the large number of calls, applications, and email inquiries we are receiving. We are no longer answering phone calls and are doing all communications with adopters via email. If you have a dog you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application before sending us emails. When your application has been processed, you will receive an email from us with further instructions on how to adopt. You do not need a new application for every dog that you are interested in adopting. 

At MAMCO we understand that in order to continue rescuing moms and babies, we must stretch our finances as far as we are able. For this reason we use variable adoption pricing. By assigning higher adoption fees to high demand moms and puppies, we are able to rescue more families in need.The money raised through these adoptions acts as a benefactor to moms and puppies in our care who require expensive veterinary treatments, have behavioral issues, or need more time to find a home. We often reduce the adoption fees on these harder-to-place moms and puppies to help them find forever families. Adoption fees vary, but all include spay or neuter, microchip, up to date vaccinations and deworming, rabies vaccine at the time of spay or neuter, and 30 days of pet insurance. We also cover hernia repair and cherry eye repair at the time of spay or neuter. Applications can be filled out at mamcorescue.org.

animal.description:
Pikachu has a sweet yet playful personality and is very gentle and smart. When she is afraid, she will hide, but if you are patient, her curiosity gets the best of her as she will come out to see what's going on. Pikachu can be unsure of humans at first but is very comfortable following and trying to play with other dogs. Once she builds trust with her new family, she will follow you and try to snuggle up next to you on the couch. She is very good at going potty outside but still has a few accidents here and there. She doesn't quite understand leashes yet so a fenced yard is ideal. Pikachu will be a loyal companion and would do best in a household with previous experience with dogs.

Approved Applicants may make the adoption fee payment by clicking donate above. Partial adoption fees will not hold a dog.

If upon meeting the dog of your choosing at an adoption event you find that you aren't a good match, your deposit will be refunded minus a 10% administration fee.

In-person adoptions will begin on the date of a dog's first event provided they are still available. Dogs not adopted during their first event will attend additional events thereafter until adopted. 

An adoption application online is required prior to viewing our dogs. Adoption fees include vaccines up until time of adoption, microchip, spay/neuter and 1st 30 days of free Pet insurance. We are not affiliated with Pet First pet insurance. (you have to sign up for the insurance or it will not go into effect). Adopters can go to our vet for medical issues that may arise in 1st 3 days of adoption. 

The dogs in our care are fostered in Colorado, Texas, and New Mexico. While all dogs are picked up during our scheduled times, sometimes transport dates change due to unforeseen circumstances.

animal.description:
LOOKING FOR ADOPTIVE HOME ASAP IN NE/CO/WY

 HAVANA 

 Located in the Sidney, NE area 
 American Pit Bull Terrier 
 2 years old 
 Dog friendly
 Good with cats 
 Kid friendly 
 House trained 
 Crate trained and knows basic commands 
 She will be completely vetted February 10th
 50 lbs approx 

Back in December we saw Havana being advertised locally on fb because her people were going through a major life change and had to move to low-income housing where animals were not allowed. We (as well as her owner) were concerned due to her breed (and because she wasnt spayed) as to where she could possibly end up. We reached out, and Havanas owner agreed she would be better off in rescue. 

Havana is amazing dog. She has been with us for a little over a month now while we get all her vetting done (will be done February 10) and we have fallen in love with her sweet personality. She is a super sweet, loving and well-behaved pitty princess. 

We were told Havana does well with other dogs; and we know she lived with multiple cats and kids. She LOVES to be outside (but does require an inside home). 

Shes a mid sized girl. Crate trained, potty trained, and your all around perfect girl. 

If interested in Havana please contact us! 

 To Contact Us 
 TEXT Cilena at 308-249-4308
 Message us through our website http://www.highplainspaw.org
 Message the Facebook Page at https://www.facebook.com/HighPlainsPAW
 Fill out our Adoption Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/adoption-application
 Email us at highplainspaw@gmail.com

 $200.00 Adoption Fee 
(Which is considered a non refundable donation and being we are a 501c3 organization it is tax deductible. The fee itself is not negotiable, our vets don't negotiate and thus neither do we).

 WE DO NOT HAVE A FACILITY ALL OUR DOGS ARE LOCATED IN FOSTER HOMES. This means there is no place for you to go in person to view our dogs. We ask that an application be filled out and we will go from there!

 Posted by Cilena

animal.description:
Let's all give a little shout-out for seniors with style! Max is a 14-year old Pomapoo (Pomaranian/Toy Poodle mix) that has a story or two to tell... This dreamboat has clearly gotten better with age and would love a new home where he can relax in his golden years! Max has had a lot of time to develop friendly social skills so he gets along with everyone - strangers, men, women, and children. He gets on well with small dogs (no big boys, please!) and cats too! I'm not sure if you can tell from the photo, but this this fella still has some pep in his step! Calm but curious, this tiny 10 lb. senior will take off faster than you might imagine, so he'll need a fenced yard to help him stay safe. Max doesn't like to talk about this but, well, as an aging guy he experiences some "senior moments" having to do with potty time. We'll be learning more about this as he settles in with his foster family. In the meantime, keep in mind that belly bands are simple solutions for our older pets! They are an affordable, comfortable option to help keep things tidy around the house. This senior sweetheart has just joined his Muddy Paws foster family so we'll have updates coming soon! 

The suggested adoption donation for Max is $300. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes. 

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver. 

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months. 

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

Peanut is a 5-month-old, 30-pound male terrier mix who came to us all the way from Texas to look for his forever home!

Peanut is a typical curious puppy who gets along with all humans and dogs. Peanut loves his crate and sleeps in it through the night. He is energetic and playful, has to investigate everything on his walk. Peanut will be a perfect addition to an active family who will spend a lot of time teaching him how to be a good puppy! 

Peanut is not yet house trained, but his foster parents are working on it.

Vaccinated for rabies, DA2PP, and bordetella. Neutered and heartworm negative. Needs microchip. Flea, tick, and heartworm prevention due 2/1.

Please contact us DIRECTLY using the instructions below if you are interested in adopting one of our Waggytails! Visit our website (www.waggytailrescue.org) for an adoption application. It is important to fill out an application as soon as possible for consideration, and we require a complete application for you to meet an animal. 

Adoptions: waggyadopt@gmail.com

Waggytail Rescue CANNOT guarantee the exact age of any adoptable dog, or final size of any of our adoptable puppies. We rely on the information provided to us by veterinarians, shelters, owner surrenders and other circumstances bringing the dog into our rescue.

AT PEPPERMINT PIG ANIMAL RESCUE, WE UPDATE ALL OF OUR PETS ON A REGULAR BASIS TO REFLECT THEIR AVAILABILITY.

IF YOU SEE ME HERE, I AM AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION. PLEASE READ MY BIO BELOW TO LEARN MORE ABOUT ME AND HOW TO APPLY TO ADOPT :)

Meet the E pups:: 8 weeks old 2/6/21, 4 to 5 pounds, 3 males, 4 females, Boxer/Chihuahua/Dachshund mixes.

Accepting Applications for adoption on 2/6/20.

These adorable little babies are lucky to be alive after the owner of their mom, who is a Chihuahua/Dachshund mix, didn't have her spayed and she bred with a boxer mix. The mom nearly died giving birth to puppies that were too big for her little body but luckily she got to the vet in time for an emergency C-section (and SPAY). Although some of the puppies sadly didn't make it, we are grateful that these, and their mother (mom is still in owner's care), survived.

These babies have a ton of personality and spunk and they're learning so much in their foster home. They are all outgoing and playful and would do well with an active family who will keep them busy and learning new things. They will likely be medium sized when fully grown.

$195 Adoption Fee. 

A $10.00 non-refundable application fee is required to submit your adoption application and will be deducted from your adoption fee if you adopt.

All puppies are dewormed, started on heartworm and flea prevention, and microchipped.

All puppies will be adopted with current, age appropriate vaccines, given by Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue. Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue will provide their puppy series DAPP vaccines, given at 8, 12, and 16 weeks of age.

Puppy adopters will be will be required to bring the puppy back to Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue to receive any remaining puppy vaccines after adoption. 

Puppy adopters will also be required to bring the puppy to our vet for their spay/neuter surgery after they receive their 16 week vaccination. 

The spay/neuter and puppy vaccines are included with the puppy adoption fee.

We have a strict one hour puppy adoption radius, puppy adopters must be within one hour of Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue. Please see our Adoption Radius tab on our website for more info, here:
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/adoption-radius/

Along with other criteria evaluated in the adoption application, a Fenced Yard is required to adopt. 

Please see our Fenced Yard Requirements tab on our website for more information, here:
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/fenced-yard-requirements/

TO CHECK AVAILABILITY of any of our adoptable animals, please go to our available pets tab, here: https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/available-pets-for-adoption/

All pets listed here are updated regularly to reflect their availability.

ADOPTION APPLICATION INSTRUCTIONS FOR PEPPERMINT PIG ANIMAL RESCUE:

Before completing the application, please read our ADOPTION PROCESS tab on our website, here: 
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/how-our-adoptions-work/

To complete our easy online adoption application, please visit our website at PeppermintPigAnimalRescue.org.

Adoption events are held every Saturday in our thrift store from 1:00pm to 4:00pm. Please complete your adoption application in advance so our volunteers have time to screen and contact potential adopters.

IMPORTANT: All applications are reviewed in the order they are received and qualifications are based on best fit for each individual pet. A volunteer will contact you if you are selected for a meet with adoptable pet. Final approval is always made in person.

Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue is a no-kill rescue. Please consider sponsoring a pet or donating to our cause. Click the DONATE tab on our website to learn more about how you can help. THANK YOU!

here
to fill out an application.
Hello! We are Greta and Peanut! We are at Cara because our parents passed away just weeks ago :( we are the best senior duo! We don't have any major health concerns that Cara can tell! We are both super duper sweet, well behaved and quiet!!!! We just need a cozy home with someone that loves being with affectionate dogs!! We do well with dogs and cats and respectful kids!!! To see more animals for adoption, please visit the CARA Website

Our adoption fees are:
Dogs: $155
Cats: $95
Puppies under 4 months: $115 plus S/N Deposit: $100
Kittens under 4 months: $70 plus S/N Deposit: $100

All pets available for adoption have been spayed or neutered (unless under 4 months please read about our adoptions
here
), are current on vaccinations and preventatives, and micro-chipped. Cats have been tested and confirmed negative for Feline AIDS and Leukemia. Dogs have been tested for heartworm disease.

Our shelter is located at 42 Deep River Rd in Sanford and is open Tues, Thurs, & Fri from 3pm - 7pm & Sat from 10-2pm (other times available by appointment). CARA's adoption process and online application can be found at
http://www.cara-nc.org/info/adoption

Please call 919-774-9433, email adoptions@cara-nc.org, or visit www.cara-nc.org for information about this or other pets available for adoption.

If you would like to adopt me or any of my friends, please visit CARA to fill out an on-line application or e-mail us at adoptions@cara-nc.org.

Every animal that comes into the CARA program is here because one or more events occurred that led to this animal needing not only a home, but a person or family to love and protect them. Each animal has been loved and cared for by a small and determined group of people who want nothing more than to know each animal is safe for the rest of his or her life. Thank you for looking to adopt!

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Chris and I’m a 5 year old chocolate/Chesapeake Lab mix (I think)! I came to SCLRR after my owner passed right around Christmas, but I persevered and found a really nice foster family to help me get in tip-top shape. Since being rescued, I have had a few lumps removed, but the vets said they turned out not to be the bad kind. Yay! I also lost a couple pounds – but I’m still a big boy weighing in around 110 pounds.

As I mentioned, I go by Chris and if you’re lucky, I’ll respond to Christopher. I have a decent amount of energy and like to go on 2-3 walks a day (20-30 min each). But I’ll settle for 2 short walks…as long as I get out to explore, I’m happy. I’m working on not tugging so much on the leash and the pinch collar really helps with that! I can sit and stay when asked, but only when I’m really paying attention. I’m a friendly guy and love people (and my foster dog brother too). I might do well with other dogs, but it’s best to meet first just in case.

I’m not a fan of cats or other animals – they distract me from listening because I just want to catch them! I’d do well with teenagers, but I’ve never been around little kids. Plus I’m a big guy who might knock them over. I’m not food driven and don’t beg at meal times. I’m house broken and know how to use a doggy door.

I wouldn’t make a good guard dog because I don’t really bark when people ring the doorbell. And MOST importantly, I’m very affectionate and don’t know anything about personal space. I love snuggling in bed with my people and following them around wherever they go!

animal.description:
Kane, which in welsh means warrior, earned his name by breaking free from the horrible past he used to live! This sweet boy has spent his entire life on a chain tied to a tree in a backyard in rural North Carolina. After some convincing, the owners agreed to surrender him to our rescue and now this two-year-old, 65 lb. pittie is up in Connecticut ready to find his happily furever after! 

Being an outdoor dog his whole life, Kane's finally adjusting to life inside a cozy foster home. Like most pit bulls, this guy LOVES love! He is as affectionate as can be and will jump up and give you a hug, while gently licking your hand. He will look up at you with his golden brown eyes and you can just feel the love he has to give. Kane knows he's finally safe and will thank you for years to come. In addition to being a cuddler, he loves a game of fetch and running around the yard. He is an energetic boy who enjoys adventures, chewing on a kong with peanut butter, belly rubs, and laying in the sun!

Since he has never lived as a normal dog, he would benefit from some training classes as he is pulls on leash and jumps when excited. Kane's currently in a home with children so we believe he'll be fine with kids 8+ as long as they're dog savvy. He would do best in a home with no other dogs as he's still learning how to interact and play. You MUST have a fenced yard to be considered for his adoption. Dog exprerience highly preferred.

Kane's adoption fee is $350 and he is up to date on vaccines, microchipped, heartworm negative, and neutered. If you are interested in adopting this sweetheart of a dog, please complete the application at form.jotform.com/200883908893166. For questions, please email info@happilyfureverafter.org.

Mindy was left to die in the backyard of her home along with her Momma and brother when her owner moved away and just left them imprisoned in the yard without food, water or any chance of survival. Rather than die the slow death that was planned for her, Mindy was rescued by a neighbor and now she is ready to start the second chapter of her life. And the rest of Mindy's story will be happy! Mindy is a gorgeous pup who will light up her forever home. If you would like to star in the rest of Mindy's life, please apply online to adopt Mindy (TX) at www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org.

animal.description:
Hello! My name is Roscoe and I am a super sweet Chi-Terrier mix looking for a new family to love.

I am 6 years old, weighing 17 lbs. and originally hail from Louisiana. I've only been a Canadian for a short while, but I'm loving all this snow!

I am calm, friendly and very well mannered. I love to chill out and snuggle next to you on the couch, especially if you are giving me belly rubs. I never get enough of those. Add a blanket to the mix and I'm in absolute heaven. My foster family knows how happy this makes me because I give them lots of kisses and stare lovingly with my big button eyes. I also love to sit by the window and watch the world go by. I especially love it when I see people and other dogs walk by. I get excited because I want to say hello. I'm ready for a new friend anytime! 

I love to chill, but I also have a playful side. I can never have enough toys. Once you get me going, I can be quite the silly dog. My foster family loves to horseplay and I get right in there. I've got a big heart and so I get along with kids and other dogs. Even though I haven't been around cats, my foster mom thinks I would be ok around them.

Canadian winters don't bother me, so I'm ready for a walk anytime of the day. I get pretty excited about walks and will wait at the door patiently until you are ready. I am really good on my leash. My foster mom is so impressed because I just trot along without pulling. I'm always crossing my paws that I can meet other people and dogs on our walks. I am house trained and can sleep in my crate every night, however, I've convinced my foster parents to let me sleep in my bed next to them. They tell me it's because I'm such a good boy!

I think I make a great companion and have lots of love to share with my forever family. I am currently being lovingly fostered in Woodbridge Ontario.

animal.description:
Ryder
Breed: Australian Cattle Dog
Age: 1.5 Years Old +/-; Neutered Male
Medical: Up to Date on Vaccinations, Microchipped, Spayed, Wormed
Weight: 40 pounds
Dogs: Yes
Cats: Unknown 
Kids: 12 +
Crate Trained : Yes
House Trained : In Progress
Location: Maine
Ryder is a strikingly beautiful boy with a larger than life personality. This happy-go-lucky guy is up for anything. Need a sidekick for your motorcycle sidecar? He’ll look great in goggles. Want a co pilot for your dream road trip? He can’t wait to get his head in the wind. Hiking? Let’s go! Is a kissy-face lovebug what you’re looking for? He’s all that and more. “Yes!” I hear you saying. “Yes, I want a beautiful, kissy-face, Epic Adventure Dog.”  Not so fast. Like many young Cattle Dogs, Ryder is mouthy. And when I say mouthy, I mean CATTLEGATOR. Your hands, feet, ears - they are all chew toys as far as Ryder is concerned. Sleeves, pant legs, mittens...it’s all fair game to him. Because of his mouthiness, families with young children will not be considered for Ryder. 

Let’s talk about dog friends. Ryder loves meeting new dogs, but the feeling may not be mutual. He is….over exuberant, to say the least. Until he’s had lots of socialization practice, Ryder’s dog friends will have to be extremely confident, tolerant, and fans of rough play. He does not have much of an off-switch when it comes to other dogs, but does rest quietly in his crate when he (or you) needs some down time. Ryder loves toys and has shown no toy or food guarding behavior with his foster siblings. 

Ryder has not yet mastered house-training, but he’s working on it and he is a fast learner.  He is still a few pounds underweight, which is good news, because he is very food motivated, and you won’t have to count calories while doling out all those training treats. Time and lots of positive training will smooth away Ryder’s rough spots, and polish what he is: an amazing, funny, sunny-natured boy with so much love to give. So….that adventure? He’s ready when you are. 

If you are interested in adopting Ryder please email sln2310@yahoo.com and request an application. Once your application has been received and reviewed, you will be contacted via email or phone by one of our volunteers. After your application is approved, the foster parent for the dog you have selected will contact you to answer any questions you may have and determine if that dog is a good match for your family. 
If you have no particular dog in mind, we will be happy to keep your application on file and notify you if the right dog should come into rescue. Catahoula Rescue of New England is an all-volunteer group. Dogs in our program are fostered by volunteers. The foster homes care for our dogs as if they were their own. All dogs have received vaccinations appropriate to age and are spayed or neutered. 
Ryder’'s adoption donation is $400 which includes Rabies, DHLPP, Bordetella, fecal test, heartworm test when appropriate and is on preventative, Spay/Neuter and microchip. We do not have a physical shelter, all of our dogs are fostered in individual foster homes across the New England and Canada

animal.description:
PLEASE VISIT OUR WEBSITE AT WWW.PITRESCUE.ORG FOR INFORMATION ON OUR ORGANIZATION, ADOPTION POLICIES AND PROCESS, EDUCATIONAL INFORMATION, AND A FULL LIST OF OUR ADOPTABLE DOGS ALONG WITH PHOTOS AND FULL BIOS!!!
More pictures and info on this particular dog visit: https://www.pitrescue.org/brigid

Apply online: http://fs22.formsite.com/siouxempire/form1/index.html?1316620486706

*Adoption application must be filled out with home visit and references (personal and vet) required prior to any adoption. Filling out an application does not obligate you to adopt, but merely begins the process. SEPR DOES adopt out of state!

Adoption fees: All SEPR adoptions are $300 for adults and $400 for puppies 1 year and under.  This includes: adoption fee (spay/neuter, utd vaccinations, micro-chipping), microchip registration, Gentle Leader, and two tie downs for use in your home. 

SEPR requires all adopted dogs attend a training class with their adoptive family within 90 days of their adoption. If an adoptive family completes this training class, they will be refunded $100 of their adoption fee with proof of licensed certificate. SEPR even offers an obedience class called Train-A-Bull to alumni over 1 year of age on a seasonal basis.  These classes are currently free!

*All other pets in the residence must be spayed or neutered and all pets up to date on vaccinations.

*SEPR requires all applicants must be 21 years of age.

*SEPR dogs are adopted to be inside the home, “part of the family” dogs only.

*Families with children 5 years of age and under wanting to adopt puppies will be reviewed on a case by case basis. Raising a puppy properly takes a lot of time, and we understand that in families with small children, time can be a limited commodity.

Accepting Applications for adoption on 2/6/20.

These adorable little babies are lucky to be alive after the owner of their mom, who is a Chihuahua/Dachshund mix, let her breed with a boxer mix and the mom nearly died giving birth to puppies that were too big for her little body. Luckily our rescue partners at Love of Paws acted quickly and got her into the vet for an emergency C-section (and SPAY). Although some of the puppies sadly didn't make it, we are grateful that these, and their mother (mom is still in owner's care), survived.

These babies have a ton of personality and spunk and they're learning so much in their foster home. They are all outgoing and playful and would do well with an active family who will keep them busy and learning new things. They will likely be medium sized when fully grown.

$195 Adoption Fee. 

A $10.00 non-refundable application fee is required to submit your adoption application and will be deducted from your adoption fee if you adopt.

All puppies are dewormed, started on heartworm and flea prevention, and microchipped.

All puppies will be adopted with current, age appropriate vaccines, given by Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue. Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue will provide their puppy series DAPP vaccines, given at 8, 12, and 16 weeks of age.

Puppy adopters will be will be required to bring the puppy back to Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue to receive any remaining puppy vaccines after adoption. 

Puppy adopters will also be required to bring the puppy to our vet for their spay/neuter surgery after they receive their 16 week vaccination. 

The spay/neuter and puppy vaccines are included with the puppy adoption fee.

We have a strict one hour puppy adoption radius, puppy adopters must be within one hour of Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue. Please see our Adoption Radius tab on our website for more info, here:
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/adoption-radius/

Along with other criteria evaluated in the adoption application, a Fenced Yard is required to adopt. 

Please see our Fenced Yard Requirements tab on our website for more information, here:
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/fenced-yard-requirements/

TO CHECK AVAILABILITY of any of our adoptable animals, please go to our available pets tab, here: https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/available-pets-for-adoption/

All pets listed here are updated regularly to reflect their availability.

ADOPTION APPLICATION INSTRUCTIONS FOR PEPPERMINT PIG ANIMAL RESCUE:

Before completing the application, please read our ADOPTION PROCESS tab on our website, here: 
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/how-our-adoptions-work/

To complete our easy online adoption application, please visit our website at PeppermintPigAnimalRescue.org.

Adoption events are held every Saturday in our thrift store from 1:00pm to 4:00pm. Please complete your adoption application in advance so our volunteers have time to screen and contact potential adopters.

IMPORTANT: All applications are reviewed in the order they are received and qualifications are based on best fit for each individual pet. A volunteer will contact you if you are selected for a meet with adoptable pet. Final approval is always made in person.

Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue is a no-kill rescue. Please consider sponsoring a pet or donating to our cause. Click the DONATE tab on our website to learn more about how you can help. THANK YOU!

For questions or inquiries on our adoptable pets, please feel free to contact our volunteer rescue team directly by submitting a Contact Form from our website, here: https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/contact-us/

animal.description:
While he may be shy at first, Rodney warms up quickly with some scratches behind the ears and is undoubtedly the sweetest hound dog. He's young about 2 years of age, but has a mild temperament and a medium 46 lb build. Rodney can be a reserved guy around people he doesn't know, but gets along with every dog he meets, and doesn't even seem to take issue with the farm's chickens. He would love to find a home with a fenced yard, and maybe even a calm canine companion who can show him the ropes. With spring just around the corner, Rodney is ready to find a home where he can blossom. Just maybe that home is with you!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Mark (TX) is a male Shepherd mix rescued in Texas. Our veterinary partner estimates that Mark is 3 months old at the time of intake in January 2021. Mark is good with people and other dogs. Mark was abandoned with his Momma and sister in the backyard of their home when their owner moved out and just left them to fend for themselves with no food, no water, no way to survive. A guardian angel was watching over Mark, though, as a neighbor intervened and made sure that Mark and his family were rescued. And now Mark is a Rescue Dogs Rock NYC pup and his life will be happy. Mark is a happy, playful little guy who doesn't want to waste one single minute of the fantastic life we promised him. If you can open your heart and home to this adorable boy, please apply online to adopt Mark (TX) at www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org.

These babies are a 'whoops' litter of Belgian/German Shepherd + ? mixes.
They are expected to be very large & smart dogs as adults, (there's a reason why the police & military choose Shepherds!) so priority will be given to large breed experienced, active adopters who are committed to a training program, can provide adequate daily exercise, do not have children under 5 years old & preferably have a securely fenced yard.

Included in their adoption fee is an initial comprehensive veterinary examination, age-appropriate vaccinations, parasite screening with treatment if needed, flea/tick treatment if needed, microchip, spay/neuter, plus any other medication or treatment needed up until the day of adoption.

animal.description:
***Please DO NOT send us inquiries/emails asking if this dog is still available. If a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder- we are still accepting applications for them**

Lola is in a foster home in Portland, OR

Lola, 10 years old, female, Labrador retriever mix, 46 lbs. Sweet senior Lola was owner surrendered to a high kill shelter in Houston Texas. Thankfully a foster reached out before this pup ended up on the euthanasia list. Lola transported to Oregon early January to settle in before finding her perfect home. 

Lola was in a foster home with a lot of other dogs in Texas. Due to the other dog's behaviors and energy Lola did not interact with them. Her current foster home has no other animals. She has met some dogs through her fenced in yard. She has passed by other dogs on walks. She would need to meet any resident dog on a meet and greet to see how she interacts. 

Lola really enjoys going on walks. Her foster has spent some time helping her to not pull on leash. She tends to get distracted and go off in various directions. Lola may be a "senior" but she has lots of energy! 

She is housebroken and doesn't mind a crate. She loves to play with her toys- tug of war is her favorite. She is food motivated so this has greatly helped with training. 

Her current foster reports no separation anxiety. Lola has been okay alone in the house. She also rides great in the car. She is very affectionate and sweet. 

Lola is an older dog with a fair amount of energy. We would love to find her a home that will keep her forever. She may need some training on leash, but appears to be very trainable. 
We have no history with kids and recommend a home with kids 12 years and older. 

***Listed BREED and AGE - We are taking our best guess on age, breed and size when fully grown. We rarely know a dog's exact age nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. ***

The first step in our process is filling out an application. We will review your application as soon as we are able- there are two of us and we do the best that we can. We review applications on a first come first serve basis and look for the best fit/match for the dog and applicant.

https://heartoftheunderdog.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Claudia is a quiet, demure adult Chihuahua mix looking to find her place in this big ole' world. She isn't a fan of the craziness of the farm and would love to find herself a quiet, adult only home where she can live peacefully in some lucky lap. At just 8 lbs, she is certainly lap-sized! Claudia is quiet in her crate, but when it's time to come out will become the cutest tiny wigglebutt ready to climb in your arms as you open the door. In her playgroup, she gets along well with the other small dogs on the farm but would be perfectly happy to be the only canine in your home, to be showered in all your undivided attention. Claudia can't wait to find herself her own peaceful little slice of paradise, so be sure to submit your adoption request if you think that just might be at your home!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
***COVID 19 NOVEMBER 2020 PROTOCOL***

Due to the surge of Covid 19 and statewide restrictions, we are adopting to LOCAL (CLALLAM AND JEFFERSON COUNTY) RESIDENTS ONLY. We are not doing adoptions to Canada at this time due to the border closure. We do not ship animals. 

OPHS is appointment only. All potential adopters must fill out an adoption application prior to setting up an appointment to meet the animal. An application can be found on our website  https://www.ophumanesociety.org/dog-adoption-application

We have limited staff during this time, please allow 3-5 business days for us to process your application. We are screening the applications for the first BEST fit for each animal. 

If you are approved, you will be contacted by us via phone or email to schedule an appointment.

NAME: Cinnamon
AGE: About 1 year
WEIGHT: About 50 lbs
BREED(S): Shepherd mix?
REASON FOR ARRIVAL: Transfer from CA

GENERAL INFO ABOUT PERSONALITY: Cinnamon is sweet with a little bit of spice. When she came in she was very fearful and wouldn't walk outside on a leash. She has made good progress and is now walking fairly well on leash and has been meeting other large dogs. 

So far she has been pretty good with other dogs, but is a little rough and rude at first. We figure she is no older than 1 year so she still has a lot of learning to do about the world. She will need someone to help build her confidence as well as train her on all of the basics, she doesn't even know sit yet (but we are working on it!).

Cinnamon has a dental condition called Enamel Hypoplasia which greatly affects the integrity of the teeth. Because of this, Cinnamon will need frequent (maybe yearly) dental exams and cleanings which could add up cost wise. This will need to be managed throughout her lifetime to ensure she stays happy and healthy. 

Activity Level? Medium
Training Needs? High
House Trained? Unknown
Leash Trained? Mostly
Comfortable with kids? Unknown
Comfortable with strangers? Shy at first
History with other dogs? Fairly good
History with cats? Unknown

Additional MEDICAL notes: Has Enamel Hypoplasia. Will need to have frequent dental exams and cleaning throughout her life compared to a regular dog.
Additional BEHAVIOR notes: None

ADOPTION FEE: $150 for an adult dog.

Adoption fee includes: Spay/neuter, initial vaccines, a microchip, rabies vaccine when appropriate, and one free veterinary visit with a local participating clinic.

Being the sweet and laid back girl she is, Lucy would prefer if new people approach her slow and gentle, just like she does to them. Once you're acquainted, make sure to give her all the ear scratches possible!

animal.description:
Meet KING JACK!!
-approximately 5 years old
-Male
-Stafford/Vizsla MIX

King is:
-Energetic
-Dominant
-Playful
-Loving
-Kind
-Adventurous!
-Timid/Skittish around MEN (at first)
-Potty Trained
-Leash Trained
-House Trained
-Good with other dogs
-Good with kids of all ages!
-NOT GOOD WITH CATS

King Jack is exactly what his name suggests, a KING! He is dominant, but also enjoys to be the baby at times. He absolutely LOVES his humans and will try to be around you at all times! Although he is energetic, he is not loud! He will occasionally make some noise when he gets excited, but don't be afraid of his bark, the king is just trying to make some friends!!

He knows basic commands such as sit, stay, come and go, but he needs someone to stay on track with his training. The king in him can be a bit stubborn at times! He will also require a SLOW INTRODUCTION TO MEN. He is fearful of men at first so he will bark and growl for a few minutes. After he is used to the men, he calms down and will enjoy some pets from them!

Over all, King Jack aims to please his people. He will say hello and will cuddle up next to you. He has gentle eyes and soft paws that are bound to steal your heart!

King's personality will shine brightest with:
-An ACTIVE family
-Someone willing to continue training
-A FENCED IN yard
-A home where going to doggy parks and the outdoors are a thing!

*A note from his foster: "Jack likes to be pet constantly and is not shy about showing it. He loves to go on long walks and see new things. "

If you believe KING JACK is the dog for you please fill out an adoption application: https://form.jotform.com/93263081961156

IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS PLEASE EMAIL INFO@MERCYFULLPROJECTS.ORG OR TEXT (786) 548-0651

If you don't know about my breed I will be very active and will require an active lifestyle. I am bred to herd animals and love having job. I am outgoing and I will follow my foster mom anywhere she goes! She has these big things called horses and I don't mind them even though they kind of scare me! I love to play with toys, chew on toys, and rough house. I am doing well with crate training and working towards potty training.

animal.description:
Meet Kiran Brighteyes, a very special boy with a heart of gold.

Kiran is a gorgeous 10 month old pit bull that weighs about 50lbs and is still growing. This amazing pup has suffered through some hard times, but healed in a loving foster home. Kiran is such a wonderful boy and charms everyone he meets. This perfect pup is quirky, fun, intelligent, loving and trainable. He is high activity, perfectly house trained, loves all over dogs and adores children! Read on to learn more about Kiran.

Kiran is currently being fostered in Olympia, Washington and is available for meet and greets with approved adopters. To apply, please fill out an application at www.doggedly.org/adoption-app

Kiran had a very sad beginning, found as a stray back in September of 2020 in Houston, Texas. Kiran was standing in a grocery store parking lot searching for trash to eat. He was extremely emaciated, covered in open bloody sores and caked in dried urine and feces after recently being dumped by his owner, likely after being locked in a kennel his entire life. From the beginning, there was something special about this gentle dog. He allowed his rescuer to scoop him up and tend to his wounds immediately. Although he was frightened, Kiran had the most amazing temperament. He was extremely sweet, docile and just wanted to be loved, despite what humans had put him through.

Kiran grew into the most loving dog when he joined his foster family. This dog is a total love bug. Kiran loves everyone that he meets, but can be a little shy at first. He gains confidence daily and is extremely dog friendly. Kiran absolutely adores children, and loves to snuggle. After this boy gets in his daily exercise, he is a complete snuggle bug, who enjoys spending his time in your lap like a giant baby. Kiran loves to sleep in bed with you and is the best snuggler, who will lay his head on your chest. It's heartwarming and also heartbreaking to think that a dog who loves people this much was ever abandoned on the streets in such poor condition.

Training wise, Kiran is a dream dog. He is kennel trained, leash trained and absolutely perfect in the car. He can be a little wild at times in normal puppy fashion, but is an extremely smart boy who loves to please. He would thrive in a home with another confident, friendly dog. Kiran is great with both males and females. He is also respectful, and even submissive, to kitties in the home. Outdoors, he will chase anything, cats and horses included, but just because he wants to play, play, play! Kiran would adore hanging out at dog parks, is wonderful with doggy introductions and is a fun, bouncy boy who enjoys adventures. Kiran is very athetlic and currently enjoys 10 mile hikes and trail runs with his foster mom. He requires a high activity home that can give him adequate exercise he needs to balance with his snuggle buddy home life.

This incredible boy is one that you do not want to miss out on! He is an absolute gem and will not last long! Apply today to make Kiran your very best friend!

animal.description:
Sophie is a beautiful, super-sweet, well-mannered older girl. She is not full corgi, but it is believed she is part corgi / part miniature Australian Shepherd.  She lived with her first family for the first 9 years of her life, then she was surrendered to CCK. She has lived with her foster family for the past 1 ½ years. About a year ago she developed a dislike for another female dog in her current home. Despite efforts taken to mitigate the issue, Sophie has persisted in her dislike. Although her family loves her very much and finds this step very difficult to take, they believe she would be happier in a home where she can be the only dog.

PERSONALITY: Sophie has an active, bright and alert personality. She loves to be petted and cuddled and loves to be near her person. She enjoys being a lap dog for short periods of time, although she will fall asleep in a lap from time to time. She does show a preference to women but does also respond to most men. She is tolerant of and even enjoys playing with young, active children if they are respectful of her. She is very active and will play fetch with a tennis ball, although her sessions last only 10 minutes or so. She is a destroyer of toys and loves nothing better than to de-squeak and de-stuff a toy. Due to her diminutive size and activity level, people have mistaken her for a much younger dog. 

SOCIALIZATION:  Sophie does not seem to have been well-socialized when she was young. She does not do well with other dogs she is not familiar with, and has had issues with a female corgi in the home she is in currently in. She sometimes will take an instant dislike to certain people, usually men. She walks well on a leash but becomes anxious when she sees another dog approaching and will vocalize loudly. She is OK in the car although she does not enjoy car rides. Sophie would prefer that strangers not approach the stopped car while she is inside. She does not like drive-thru’s and will vocalize loudly if she can hear a voice through a speaker or see someone at a window, close to the vehicle.

TRAINING: Sophie is perfectly house trained and is not known to have an accident in the house. She knows her name and has excellent recall. She goes out without complaint despite the weather, will take care of herself and come back immediately if necessary. She is extremely obedient and loves to please. Sophie is very smart and catches on to things very quickly. 

HEALTH:  For her age, Sophie is relatively free of many health issues. Unlike a full-bred corgi, Sophie sheds very little. She has a touch of arthritis in one knee and is taking Cosequin for this. Because of her anxious nature and the situation with the other dog in her current home she has been on Fluoxetine. This is a mild antidepressant for canine anxiety, which is relatively inexpensive.

OVERALL:  Sophie is an amazing girl who would bloom in the right environment. A quiet home with a consistent routine where she is the only pet would be ideal. She would love to be someone’s constant companion and friend!

animal.description:
Due to COVID-19, CITY DOGS is currently doing adoptions by APPOINTMENT ONLY. Please visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog to request a meet and greet! 

Questions? Email: citydogs@city.cleveland.oh.us | Call: (216) 664-3476
Visit: 9203 Detroit Avenue Cleveland, OH 44102

Hours:
10 AM - 3 PM Monday, Wednesday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday
10 AM - 6 pm Tuesday & Thursday

Fee: $61 | Includes spay/neuter, shots, microchip, license, 30 days free pet insurance (when registered upon adoption)

The CITY DOGS mission is to increase adoptions from the City Kennel by changing the image of the pit bulls who make up the majority of the kennel population, by preparing all adoptable dogs in the kennel for lives in loving homes and by creating as many opportunities as possible for the public to meet and get to know our dogs for the terrific pets they are meant to be.

Our Adoption Process...
Here's a little about how things work:
All of the CITY DOGS posted for adoption are available for direct adoption from the kennel, unless noted otherwise. You must schedule a meet with a dog in advance - we are not currently accepting walk-ins. Please look online first to see if there are any dogs you think would be a good fit for your home before scheduling a meet. To get the process started, visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog and fill out the form. One of our adoption counselors will get in touch to schedule and confirm your meet! At the kennel, an adoption counselor will introduce you and your family to the adoptable dogs, share information we know about them, and discuss our suggested ways for successfully integrating a new dog into your home. You are welcome to meet multiple dogs. If the dog you adopt is already fixed, he or she may leave with you that day - otherwise, the dog can go home after receiving the spay or neuter surgery.)

About Our Dogs: All available dogs have gone through a behavioral and medical assessment. This assessment is a snapshot of who the dog is at that given time. We cannot make any guarantees with regard to behavior, temperament or health of any City Dog once they are in the home. Most of our dogs are picked up as strays, so we do not know what kind of home environment they were living in (i.e. with kids, other dogs or other cats), nor do we know if most of them are house trained. Everything we know about them is based on volunteer and staff observations. We do have some dogs in foster homes, where they will have more information about how the dog is in a home environment. It is very hard to tell with certainty whether or not a dog will be good with kids, cats or another dog. If you have kids in the home or another dog, we do require that they be present for a meet and greet with the dog you are considering for adoption.

Heath/Vaccinations: Dogs that are adopted directly from the kennel need to go to your personal vet within two weeks of leaving the kennel. All dogs receive their DAPPL, Rabies, and Bordatella vaccines, though you may be required to get follow up boosters. All dogs come microchipped and with a Cuyahoga County license.?
