animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Boxer mix | 9-years old | 65 lbs | Adoption Fee: $225.00"Will you love me forever?" I seem to say to everyone as I gaze at them with my soulful brown eyes. My name is Lynette, and I'm a 9-year-old boxer mix from Texas. Based on the wear and tear on my body, I think I've had it kind of rough up until now, and I am looking forward to a brighter future, starting with you!

I'd love nothing more than to lay by your side (or, if you let me, on your lap) and snooze the day away. I am a world-class snuggler and hope that whoever adopts me does not need any personal space. I love to lick people's faces and will sometimes gently paw at their arms if I don't think I'm getting the attention I deserve. I also love toys, but not really to play with-I just like carrying them around and keeping them near me.

I am a sophisticated lady and always do my business outside, and I have yet to get into anything I'm not supposed to. I take direction from my humans really well, except maybe when they're trying to get me off the couch to go somewhere-I'm just so comfy!

I admit, I can be a bit cranky with other animals. Because of this, I think I'd do best as an only pet, so I can soak up all your love and attention. I also get a little distressed when there's a lot of chaos or noise. It has made me worried when I've seen rough-housing, and I've tried to intervene. So if there are kids in the home they'd need to be older, quiet, and respectful, and ideally also let me snuggle with them.

I am currently being treated for heartworm, but I am still available to Foster to Adopt. This means that you get to take me home now to keep forever, but I won't be "officially" yours until I'm done my treatment, which can take a few months. During treatment, which the rescue pays for, my only exercise can be short potty breaks. That shouldn't be a big problem for me since I am already a big couch potato, so don't let this part scare you away! Please ask the rescue if you have any questions about heartworm or heartworm treatment.

In the meantime, if you are looking for the world's best snuggle companion to keep you warm in these winter months, fill out an application to meet me today!

Completion of an Adoption Application via our website (www.RescueCrew.org) is the best way to show your interest in an animal and is the first step in the adoption process.

All companion animals adopted by The Rescue Crew are spayed/neutered, up-to-date on age appropriate vaccinations, tested for FIV/FeLK (cats) or heartworm (dogs), microchipped, dewormed and provided with monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives.

The Rescue Crew is a foster based rescue organization, meaning all of our adoptable pets are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a physical location where you can stop by to visit the animals - we require the completion of an Adoption Application prior to meeting any of our adoptable pets in foster care.

For the most complete information regarding this animal, and all of our adoptable pets, please ensure you are visiting our website directly at www.RescueCrew.org. You can also access the necessary online adoption application here as well.

animal.description:
MURPHY ~9 months old. Good with older considerate children, dogs, and cats.

GSRA adopts to residents of VA, NC, and SC only

Murphy's a very wiggly, happy, playful boy full of puppy energy. He's good with large and small dogs, he's very respectful of dogs who don't want to play with him. He also previously lived with cats but without another dog in the home he will chase the cats to try to get them to play with him. He's a good car rider, a decent leash walker - he loves to carry a stick during his walk, and is learning to settle in his crate although it's not his favorite place to be. Murphy loves to run with his foster siblings and tolerates their more dominant personalities well but will let them know when he's had enough of their chompy play style. He would do best with a fenced yard or large property to run in (he doesn't appear to have a high prey drive). He needs a playmate. He's a high energy boy who will need outlets to burn off steam so he doesn't find his own entertainment. If you think he sounds like a perfect boy you'd be right!! The only thing Murphy cannot have in his forever home are small children. If you're looking for a buddy to exercise with and then curl up on the couch for a movie and popcorn then Murphy's the guy for you.

It is GSRA policy that we do not adopt dogs under the age of 1 year to families with children under the age of 8 years old.For more information on our adoptable pet list please visit: Adoptable Pet List

Please join us at our next Event(s):

Current Scheduled Events:

animal.description:
Meet Hank! This sweet 7 year old boy is looking for his forever home! He lived in a home with two other dogs, but when one of the other dogs attacked him, his owner surrendered him at the vet. Poor Hank lost his family, and was given over to a shelter. Thanks to a wonderful foster, our rescue was able to pull him back into a home environment. Hank doesn't hold a grudge, and is still considered dog friendly. However, we believe a calmer dog would be a better companion for him as opposed to a highly energetic, hyper dog. His gentle nature would make him a wonderful family dog! We are unsure about how he would do with cats, but we can test him if needed.

Interested? Great! Submit an application at www.caninecastawaysrescue.org. The application approval process can take up to 7 business days. Once approved, we will contact you for that highly anticipated meet and greet with your whole family, including any existing dogs in your home!

Not ready to commit to being a full time fur mommy or daddy? You can apply to foster! Just fill out our foster application on our website, and be as thorough as possible so we can match you with a great fit for you and your home!

Rebel is a sweet pittie girl who was surrendered by her owner's family. Sadly, she and two other dogs lost their daddy, and their family was not able to care for them. Rebel is what we would consider a "velcro dog". She loves to be with her people, and would love a mommy or daddy who is home a lot! She does okay with other submissive dogs, but would rather have a home all to herself! She is NOT cat friendly.

Interested? Great! Submit an application at www.caninecastawaysrescue.org. The application approval process can take up to 7 business days. Once approved, we will contact you for that highly anticipated meet and greet with your whole family, including any existing dogs in the home!

Not ready to commit to being a full time fur mommy or daddy? You can apply to foster! Just fill out our foster application on our website, and be very thorough so we can match you with a great fit for you and your home!

animal.description:
Date of birth: 12/10/2019

1/30/2021: Bobby is an adorable American Staffordshire mix!  He has cute B&W markings, and we love his underbite! He is a year old and weighs 38 lbs. 

• Bobby is friendly and very playful. He’ll need daily exercise.  He’ll be a fun companion for someone wanting an active dog. And he’s a great size! 

• Bobby likes other dogs and would love to have another playful dog to play with in his home. We’d ask you to bring your dog to meet Bobby to see if they could be buddies.

• He’ll need a house with a fenced yard.

• Bobby will need a home where he’s not left alone a lot— either in a home with a person who’s home a lot, or with another dog for companionship. He seeks companionship. He does not like to be left in the yard by himself for long. 

• He needs a home without young kids. He’s bouncy and rambunctious and needs to learn more manners.

• He’s crate trained. 

• Bobby has been neutered, vaccinated, microchipped and tested for heartworms. He’s a sweet boy who’ll be a wonderful match for someone wanting an active companion for themselves and/or their dog.

MORE ON ADOPTING OUR DOGS... 

> COVID-19 UPDATE:  PLEASE SUBMIT AN ONLINE ADOPTION APPLICATION AND A MEMBER OF OUR ADOPTIONS TEAM WILL REACH OUT TO YOU.  Please visit our web site at HSGKC.ORG for an adoption application, our current COVID-19 adoption protocol, and other adoption info. 

> If you decide you'd like to adopt one of the pets you meet, we reserve the pet for you but we generally don't send the pet home with you that day. We’ll instead schedule a pick up date and time that’s convenient for you.   

> Our goal is to send you home with a healthy pet and any information and support you may need to help your new pet adjust to his or her new home.  All of our dogs & puppies have been spayed or neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, treated for fleas & ticks, tested for heartworms (7 mo. and over), and are on monthly heartworm preventative. Puppies who are too young to receive all the necessary puppy boosters and/or first rabies shot may be brought back to us for those vaccines at no extra charge. You will also receive a leash, collar, coupons for pet supplies and services, toys, and educational materials. And we'll give your dog a bath before he or she goes home! 

> Please note that we prefer and may require a fenced yard for many of our dogs.  Exceptions are made on an individual basis depending on the dog's needs, the person's dog experience, the dog's and person's activity levels, home environment and other factors. 

Thank you for searching for a shelter pet!

Dog Adoption Contact Info:
Email: christine@hsgkc.org
Phone: 913.521.2339

animal.description:
First let me say..Moyo means heart in Swahili for the only coloring on her aside her nose is the heart shaped splotch on her eye.

On Nov 21st 2021 we took in this beautiful but scared abandoned 10m old baby from Homestead FL.  About 5 days before her family was evicted and they left her out in the cold rain with the trash when they moved.  She never left the property and was terrified when the landlord came to check on things after complaints were made of the dog being abandoned. Rescues were contacted and no one stepped up ..so we did.  

She was then brought to West Palm where we began to give her the nutrition she needed, socialize her and work with her. She is now ready for that forever home.

Ideal home.. a fenced yard with another dog..shes currently with 4 females close in size..doesnt seem to like little dogs much..so a home with like size is better. 

She loves to play, tug o war, catch me if you can, fetch and just is an overall good girl.  She is crate trained and I imagine house broken. She's smart and highly trainable. Not likely the best with cats either but not certain. 

Please when sending an inquiry about her ..mention your home setting and other dogs size and age. She was born near Jan 2020. Also must give a phone number. Thank you

Please contact C.A.R.E. for more information about this pet. Moby Mastiff, Born in 2019, Neutered male Howdy! Moby the Mastiff here. I'm a very expressive guy that is the perfect mix of stubborn and sweet. My striking face makes me look like quite the dignified fellow, don't you think? My affectionate personality and outstanding leash skills are two of my best traits. In fact, I'll walk right by your side without pulling a bit, to make sure I'm protecting you from any strangers. I'm a real gentle giant, so to speak, and I'm known by my friends at CARE to be a total sweetheart. I've mastered the "sit," "shake," and "down" commands, but I'd like to learn more. Don't worry, I'm very vocal, so I'll let you know exactly what I want, and if you don't listen to me, I will plant my paws down and show you my stubborn streak. I love meeting new people and playing in the snow. Making snow angels is so much fun! Toys are a little interesting, but I'd rather be next to someone and be their loyal companion. I've been known to lay my head in volunteers' laps. I'm looking so hard to find just the right person, someone who is strong enough to handle a dog of my size and powerful strength. I hope it's you!
Adoption Information: Size: Extra Large / 80 lbs Children: No Dogs: No Cats: Unknown Experience: Needs an experienced Mastiff handler Adoption Fee: $300 This dog is neutered, microchipped and has had a full veterinary checkup and vaccines.

animal.description:
Date of birth:  12/2016

1/30/2021:  Sparrow is a pretty Black Lab mix! She’s 4 years old and she currently weighs about 50 lbs, but she should weigh about 55-60 lbs.  

• Sparrow was neglected in her previous home and was horribly underweight. We’ve included a photo of her taken when she first arrived. The poor girl weighed just 26 lbs.  We’ve put much needed weight on her and she’s close to an appropriate weight now.

• Sparrow is friendly and very playful— she acts like a puppy!  She’s got lots of energy. 

• Sparrow needs a home with a fenced yard.  She can be a barker, so she would not be a good match for an apartment.  

• Sparrow is super smart and, no surprise, she is extremely food motivated. She likes to play with balls with treats in them, and she’d love thinker toys.  She would probably love agility classes and do well in them.  

• She needs basic training. She jumps up on people, so we’re working with her on that but she’ll need continued training. As mentioned, she’s very much like a puppy and she’ll need all the guidance and training and house training that a puppy would need! 

• Sparrow would be a good match for some but not all dogs. She’d need a very playful doggie companion. If you have a dog, we’d ask you to bring your dog in to meet Sparrow to see if they could be buddies. 

• She needs a home without young kids at this point because she jumps up on people and is too rambunctious.  

• Sadly, Sparrow tested positive for heartworms. She will have her first treatment on March 8. For several weeks following she’ll need to be on restricted activity. If you are interested in fostering or adopting Sparrow, we can tell you more about her treatment plan. All costs will be covered. 

• Sparrow has been spayed, vaccinated and microchipped. She’s an extremely sweet girl who’s been through a lot — she deserves a loving home.

• She can be a barker when she wants something, so wouldn’t be a good match for an apartment.

• She can get a bit anxious here with some panting and drooling, and then drinking water and needing to go outside more often. Date of birth:  12/2015

1/30/2021:  Clover is an absolutely adorable Bull Terrier mix!  She is 5 years old and she weighs 50 lbs, but she needs to gain some weight.  Clover’s had a rough life and she ended up at KCK Animal Services. She’d had a litter of puppies and then developed mastitis (infected mammaries) and pyometra (uterine infection). We did emergency surgery to save her life. She’s healed up now and doing well.

• Clover can be timid around new people and in new places, but she warms up quickly with treats— she’s very food motivated.  Once she knows you she’s a real sweetheart!  

• Clover needs a home with someone who has dog experience (not someone who is looking for their first dog as an adult).  She’ll be a wonderful and devoted companion for the person who gives her the time and attention she deserves. 

• She can be vocal and would not be a good match for an apartment. We'd like her to have house with a fenced yard.  She is not a good candidate to take to a dog park. 

• Clover lived with another dog in her previous home, but she’s been unsure around the other dogs here.  If you have a dog, we’d ask you to bring your dog to meet Clover to see if they could be buddies.  

• She’s been reactive towards other dogs when she’s walking on a leash. She’s improving and is less reactive than when she first arrived. She'll need a home with someone who can work with her on that, and she is quite strong. 

• Clover needs a home without young kids. She also has a prey drive and needs a home without cats.

• She is crate trained.  

• Clover has been spayed, vaccinated, microchipped and tested for heartworms.  She’s a super sweet girl and she loves people— she’ll be a loving and loyal companion.

animal.description:
About 3 years old, this handsome hound mix is Finian. He has the most gorgeous white coat with the most adorable brindle patches scattered about. We are especially smitten with the cute ones on his ears! Finian is a super friendly guy with medium level energy to match his medium build, weighing about 45 lbs. Happy to join you on a long stroll around the neighborhood, some playtime in the backyard, or just binge-watching TV on the couch, Finian gets along well with the other dogs on the farm and absolutely loves people! Be sure to ask about him at your adoption appointment!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
Please read entire posting for information on our new procedures. We are currently requiring appointments for all adoptions.  Please give us a call if you questions about a pet or complete an application at https://adoptmountainpets.org/pet-services/adoption-process/application-form to make arrangements to visit the Animal Resource Center.


Meet the newest puppy crew! We do not know the exact breeds of these wonderful puppies however our best guess would be a hound/bird dog mix. With a wide range of personality and love, we hope you'll find a forever friend within this adorable litter! If you are interested in meeting the puppies please fill out an adoption application located on our website or give us a call at 970-626-2273


Adopters will be considered on the totality of the application and how it matches the particular pet's needs.


Most dogs who come from the shelter will not be house trained.

We do not know or make guarantees that a dog or cat will do well with all children, other animals or is house-trained.

We will need to talk to all of the adults in the home prior to making an appointment to visit with a pet. 

In most cases its necessary to to have family dogs come into meet your potential adoptee. Please be sure your dogs are spayed or neutered and current on vaccines (distemper - parvo and rabies) before bringing them for a meeting.

All dogs must be transported home in a travel crate to transport your new pup home safely.

Renters must provide a copy of a lease indicating pets are allowed or contact information for the landlord.


Second Chance is happy to have been providing stray, surrender, adoption, and our Community Outreach services throughout the COVID situation.   

All services are provided by appointment only.  Please do not visit the shelter without first making calling the shelter. 

For the safety of our community, staff and volunteers all visitors are required to wear masks and follow the posted social distancing processes *see below.  Do not make an appointment if you are not comfortable following these procedures.  Thank you for understanding and your support.  

If you are interested in meeting or adopting one of our pets or have questions about the process please see our website at www.adoptmountainpets.org or call the Shelter between 11:00 am and 5:45 pm Tuesday through Saturday. 970 626 2273

*  We want to provide you excellent customer service today and keep you and our team safe and healthy. Please read what we are asking you to do today to reduce the risk of spreading COVID-19:

It only takes one look in this boy's eyes to see the sweetness in his soul. Kilroy is a beautiful black lab and pit mix with a touch of white fur on his chest. He is a young fella just around a year old, but with a more reserved personality than some of his similar age and breed mix pals. Although he can be a touch shy at first meeting, it doesn't take long for this kind fella to open up and become a happy, playful pup. He is getting along well with the other dogs on the farm and enjoying attention from volunteers, but what he really wants is a home all his own. Could that home be with you?!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

Ester just arrived! Network to us from a rescue partner in the south and is approximately 4mos old. Our partners got a late night call that a puppy had been attacked by a bigger dog and needed medical help asap. The owners agreed that surrendering her to our rescue partners were in her best interest so she could get the help she needed. Ester leg is almost back to normal and she is now ready to find her forever home. After settling into foster care we have learned that Ester does not do well with other dogs most likely due to her past so
her forever home must have no other dogs.

Ester loves kids though and is very cuddly and loves to lay by your feet. She loves to play outside. And is getting the hang of potty training right away!

Breed and size once full grown is not a guarantee as she came into rescue without either parent.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Please contact Jenny Cope (giveadogahome@live.com) for more information about this pet.

Be sure to read ALL information provided.

A PET IS FOR LIFE -
THINK ABOUT THE INVESTMENT!

FEN was saved from a high kill shelter in Texas where dogs often have only 3 days to be saved. FEN is neutered rabies, core vaccines, heartworm/tick disease tested negative for all. He is de-wormed, monthly preventatives and microchipped. At the time of rescue in the middle of January 2021, he weighed around 15.00 pounds and has an estimated date of birth 7 January 2018

. We cannot say for sure what breed he is, so we expect families to do their own research on his look and size and decide what breed you think she is and if you have the lifestyle suitable for his needs.

FEN arrived at the rescue on 15th January 2021 and was lucky enough to be adopted on 18th January 2021, however, sadly on 28 January we had an email from the adopter saying things were not working out with Fen and the young daughter. He had growled at her when she was feeding him, nipped at her face (didn't break the skin) when she went to kiss him and chased her when she came out of her bedroom.

Other than these issues with the young daughter, FEN had been great, he had been to the groomer and did fantastic having a full spa, bath, nail trim, ears cleaned and teeth brushed. He has gained some very much needed weight and the family was trying to teach him what toys were.

Fen has clearly had a rough life before he ended up in the shelter, he has scars on him, was extremely skinny and just looked exhausted, no doubt from trying to survive in the extreme heat and living on the streets in El Paso. At the time of writing, Fen has only been back at the rescue for a few hours, however, he is living up in the house with 25 other dogs ranging from small terrier, up to 120 pound German Shepherds with all breeds, ages and sizes in between. He has curled up next to me on the couch and is happy just chilling out - but keeping a watchful eye on the other dogs.

Fen would benefit from a family without small children, who can le him settle and decompress from another change this poor boy has had to adapt to. He would be great as the only dog, or with another dog. Fen doesn't know how to play and the family had been trying to introduce him to toys, whilst at the rescue before his adoption he was living in a communal area with 15 other small dogs and did great and he enjoyed chewing on cow hooves.

Although a smaller dog, we are looking for a family who will take him on walks and let him explore different places and lead a physically and mentally healthy lifestyle

More pictures and possible video's can be found on his page on the rescue website.

All dogs use dog doors to go out and do their business or to enjoy the cool, fresh weather in their dog runs or communal areas. We cannot say if a dog is house-trained, however, we expect families to understand that all dogs need a transition period and accidents could happen and training is most definitely needed.

You MUST understand that dogs need time to decompress and adapt to their new environment and home. It is a HUGE transition they make from the kill shelter, being vetted, on transport for 3 days and arriving in Maine where the temperature and such is very different to what they have only known. In rescue there is what is known as the "3 Point Rule" Days 1-3 your dog is stressed, anxious, confused as to where they are now. Weeks 1-3 your dog is adjusting, settling in, learning things. At the 3 month point, your dog understands they are home, and have built up a trusting relationship where they feel loved and secure.

All dogs are fed Rachael Ray Nutrish PEAK Natural Dry Dog Food, Grain Free Western Grasslands Recipe with Bison. Rachael Ray Nutrish Peak Dog Food receives the Dog Food Advisor's second-highest tier rating of 4.5 stars.

FEN is available for adoption for an adoption fee of $550

This fee is not negotiable and is used to cover the rescue costs of pulling, vetting, health certificate, transport from Texas to Maine, monthly preventatives, supplements, food, general day to day cost of running a brick and mortar rescue and anything else that is needed. Canadian adopters need to know that customs charge 15% taxes when entering into Canada.

Due to borders being closed, it is up to families to call the US and Canadian borders to find the current details on border crossing. Animal Welfare is deemed essential in the US, but quarantine rules entering back into Canada must be followed.

If you feel that you have the heart and home to give this precious soul a wonderful life, please go to our website, under the ADOPTION INFO tab, complete, then submit the APPLICATION. Our process takes around 1-2 days, and ensuring your references are aware that we will be calling, could speed up the process. Once you have been approved, we discuss any questions in regards to the dog you are wanting to adopt, then you complete and submit the contract, make payment and then we can work out the pick up / transport arrangements.

Please do NOT submit an application if you are not looking to take home a new best friend within the next few weeks.

https://www.giveadogahome-sanantonio.org/forms/form?formid=5838

ALL Dogs are LOCATED AT THE RESCUE IN SEBEC, MAINE. We post in various states along the east coast and Canada where we have had lots of successful adoptions to enable more exposure for these beautiful saved souls. Families will need to be prepared to travel to the rescue to meet and take home their new best friend. Sebec is located just outside the towns of Dover-Foxcroft and Milo (approx 8 miles) and approx 45 miles from Bangor. There are also lots of hotels, motels, pet friendly accommodations and wonderful camp-sites for the more adventurous families and what a great way to get to know your new best friend.

Click here to watch a video of FEN-AR.

animal.description:
This STUNNING and HAPPY girl is going to make some family so happy. There is literally no way to be sad with Ruthie is around! She is silly, active, and just an all around joy to have around. 

Ruthie is a Husky - which means ACTIVE and SMART! She is seeking a family that can keep up with daily exercise and socialization. She also loves to sing the song of her people - so she's looking for a family that understands Huskies are silly breeds who need families that don't mind a little shenanigan in their life!  

Ruthie is ~8 months old and about 45 lbs. We anticipate she'll be a good sized girl in the 60 lbs range when she is done growing. She'd likely be best suited for a home environment that has a stable, fenced in yard. 

Ruthie lives with other dogs and some little humans. She would do great as part of a pack or as a solo girl as long as her family is committed to dog park dates! She is a bit interested in kitties - so a family with kitties would have to ensure a proper introduction. 

Ruthie will be fully vetted ahead of her adoption and we anticipate she'll be ready to head home within the first couple of weeks of February. 

Ruthie is still in Houston and her adoption will be a long-distance one. Ruthie will travel to her adoptive family following the application and contract process.

Ruthie's adoption fee is $500 (which includes the cost of transport) 

If you have questions about Ruthie, please email us at adoptions@reggiesfriends.org 

If you'd like to apply to adopt Ruthie, you can do so via our website at https://reggiesfriends.org/about/adoption/dogapp/

animal.description:
Angel is an adorable little dog with Dobby-ears.  Like Dobby, she is very shy and timid when meeting new people and gets anxious when there’s too much activity.  She finds comfort and security in her crate which is her haven when she’s feeling nervous.  Angel is looking for a quiet home with only adults to help her learn to trust humans again, and another small, calm dog to give her companionship.

Angel needs a family willing to be very patient and allow her to open up on her own terms.  She is very anxious when being approached or petted, she may flinch when first touched.  She has not shown much interest in playing with toys yet, but does like to play with the resident dog in her foster home as she becomes more comfortable in her environment.  She has not yet interacted with cats.

She is a good girl and is house-trained and uses a pee-pad when her humans are away too long for her tiny bladder.  Angel walks well on her leash with opportunity to stop and sniff or explore.  She loves a good car ride and lays quietly on the seat.  Even though she can be visibly nervous going to places, such as the vet, she remains well-behaved and will follow the directions of a trusted human.

Angel is very well crate-trained and also stays in a wire pen for longer periods.  It is recommended that her home be equipped with areas, that give her the opportunity to retreat to in safety when she’s feeling overwhelmed.

She is very nervous now, but with a lot of time and patience, she will be a delightful addition to her new family.  She has been through a lot in the first few years of her life and she deserves a quiet, loving home to show her that she can trust humans again and feel safe in her home and with her family.  Angel is super sweet and deserves the opportunity to spread her wings.

Requirements:
-fully secured fenced yard (no electric fence)
-no apartments
-no bark collars, shock collars, or prong collars
-no children in the home
-another calm, respectful dog under 20 lbs in the home

animal.description:
Meet Benson, he is a 7 month old, 68 lb., Great Pyrenees, looking for his forever home.  Benson is a typical puppy, he is a big love.  Benson came into rescue after being stuck by a car and left for dead.  Benson had surgery on his back hind leg, he gets along well, but he sometimes needs to be made to slowdown so he does not over strain his hind leg.  Who ever ends up adopting Benson, will need to keep him from over doing that leg.  At this time he needs nothing further done.  Benson enjoys the company of other dogs, unsure of cats, and loves his people. Best with no small children, older sturdy kids are fine. He will also need a home where the yard in fenced.  Interested adopters should fill out the application

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please apply online, at https://bigfluffydogs.com/adopt/adoption-application/. 

Our main website, www.bigfluffydogs.com has more information about us and the rescue process. 

NOTE TO EMAILERS FROM PETFINDER: WE DO NOT RESPOND TO EMAIL INQUIRIES WITHOUT AN APPLICATION. WE REGRET WE CANNOT RESPOND TO EVERY EMAIL, BUT UNLESS YOU FILL OUT AN APPLICATION, WE DO NOT KNOW YOU EXIST. 

All known information about an individual dog is provided in its listing. We do our best to provide accurate information, but adopters should understand that each home is different and the dog may behave differently in a new home. Dogs are creatures of their environment and you help make the dog what it will be. Homes considering adopting a puppy must be prepared for 1.) Flexible schedules for potty training. Puppies can only hold it for one hour per month of age (i.e. a 4-month-old puppy can only go 4 hours without a potty break). 2.) Crate training until the puppy is at least one year old to prevent chewing on inappropriate things when you can't supervise. 3.) Socialization.  The more positive and varying experiences as a puppy the better, both in and out of your home. 4.) Puppy behavior and life stages are equivalent to a human toddler. It takes at least a full year to have a calmer, well-adjusted dog. Patience is required and when your dog's behavior is a positive experience for you and those around you, your patience will be rewarded ten-fold, for years to come.  Please do not consider adopting a puppy if you have not thoroughly thought through the pros and cons of having one. So many people end up returning them after 3-5 months because they didn't realize the amount of work involved in raising a puppy.  Patience, appropriate toys, socialization, and obedience training are all musts. All are time-consuming and can be expensive. All dogs require supervision with children and obedience training. Adopters that want to have good dogs must be prepared to put the time and effort into training a dog. Any dog requires work and effort, but a well trained, well-socialized dog is more than worth the effort to get them there.

animal.description:
These puppies are labrador retriever mixes that were born on Nov. 3, 2020. Their mother (pictured) was found as a stray in Caldwell, TX and brought to our rescue. We did not realize she was pregnant until several weeks after her arrival. She had 8 beautiful puppies, as you can see! There are 4 males and 4 females. They are equally split between black and brown too! They have all had their first 2 rounds of puppy vaccines and have been dewormed. They will need 2 more boosters to be considered fully vaccinated. After adoption, we require that each puppy be spayed or neutered. You will be reimbursed a portion of the adoption fee once you provide proof of surgery from a licensed veterinarian. 

These puppies are so sweet and they are absolutely adorable!! They love everyone they meet, especially children! Each sweet baby is ready for their new loving forever home!

Our adoption process includes an application, a meeting/play date with your future fur baby, a brief home visit, and an adoption fee. Our adoption fees are in place to offset veterinary costs (spaying, neutering, vaccines, deworming, and microchipping) and to ensure our dogs will not be used for dog fighting or any other malicious purposes.

animal.description:
Zeus is a handsome boy who wants nothing more than his ball and his people. He loves to be with his family! Zeus was found running around all by himself and in pretty bad shape. He was covered in fleas and had some fur loss. He was also really skinny. He's been gaining weight, and his fur is growing back. He's looking for a family of his very own to love. He does great with kids and with dogs. He also does well with kitties with proper introductions.
If you've been looking for a very sweet and loving boy to add to your family, please consider Zeus.


ADOPTION APPLICATION: www.tinyurl.com/IADRAdoptionApp

If you'd like to help Zeus while he searches for his very own family, you can sponsor him for only $19/month here: https://petbucks.org/pet/6214/sponsor/create


***IMPORTANT- PLEASE READ***
The State of Texas requires rescues to collect sales tax on any adoption fees. Our adoption fee is $175. Texas State Sales Tax will be added to that amount.

Due to the nature of our adoption process, our fosters are usually only able to consider potential adopters within the Dallas-Fort Worth Metroplex. A vet reference is required, and a trial period will be completed before finalizing the adoption. Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description:
Lady is a very, very sweet girl who absolutely loves people. She is shy at first but VERY trusting and will warm up to you quickly. She is a HUGE cuddler and wants nothing more than to be around her humans 24/7. Lady is still a little nervous that when her humans leave they might not come back for her, so she needs someone who is willing to put in the time and energy to lessen her separation anxiety. Lady responds VERY well to positive reinforcement, and she gets nervous at aggressive behaviors like scolding and raising your voice. Her new family needs to be willing to be patient and gentle with her. She is a puppy, so she has a lot of energy and loves to play. Squeaky toys and bones are some of her favorite things. A fenced-in backyard with room to run would be encouraged.

If interested, please
complete the
Adoption Application
on our website at
www.NeedyPaws.org
and we will contact you.
Adopters must live within an hour's drive of St. Louis, MO.

Our $250 adoption fee includes up-to-date vaccinations, heartworm testing and preventative, spay/neuter and microchip.

We are a 100% foster-based rescue and all of our dogs live in approved foster homes. We are dedicated to finding the best Forever Homes, and will perform home visits and conduct veterinarian and reference checks for each potential adopter.

animal.description:
Maxwell is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Maxwell is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption. 

Age: ~9 years old
Weight: ~19lbs
Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: He has been left alone for brief periods of time in a sectioned off area (kitchen). He will take some time to settle.
Dog sociability: Maxwell lives with other dogs in his foster home and has done well, but he prefers slow intros to new friends. On walks, he is leash reactive and will bark/lunge at other dogs on walks. He is improving with training, but his adopter will want to continue to work on this!
Cat sociability: Not a match 
Kids: Unknown, but shy/fearful so older kids only
Ideal home: Maxwell is looking for a home that is comfortable to take things slow with him as he warms up over time (with lots of high value snacks!) He prefers a quiet neighborhood so he doesn't have to pass by a bunch of other dogs or people while out on their walks as he can be leash reactive (barks/lunges).

Maxwell may be the sweetest boy you'll ever meet. If his soulful brown eyes don't win you over, his gentle and cuddly demeanor certainly will. He's a calm boy who wants nothing more than to snuggle up into a fuzzy blanket with you and nap the day away. He is a big fan of medium-length walks, or wandering around a park at his own pace. He's a bit shy with new people but opens up quickly if they give him some affection. He has done great meeting new people in his foster's backyard but can be a little nervous of new folks if he is out on a walk. He won't say no to treats, but will get most excited if you scratch him on the bridge of his nose. He may sound too good to be true, but I assure you he is real and ready to find his forever home! 

Maxwell is well-behaved, sweet-natured and smart, and with enough hot dogs you could certainly teach this older dog some new tricks! 

Maxwell's adoption fee is 150. He is neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative.

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

animal.description:
Paiton is full of puppy energy!! Feisty, fearless, and smart, she needs a lot of activity to keep her happy.  She’s very sweet, loves to cuddle, and is a good kisser until she gets overexcited -- then watch your nose! Her foster family is working on her puppy nibbling by offering a toy instead. She catches on fast!

She is doing well learning to walk with harness and leash; she stays close in with a slight pull. She loves toys and plays by herself quite well. So far she has not chewed up anything. All stuffed toys are still intact. She is almost house trained and learned to use the dog door on the second time through. She is healthy and eats enthusiastically. She is also crate trained and sleeps in the crate at night.

In her foster home, she does not back down from the older, resident dog even after being warned and nipped a few times. She will probably do best in a home with a younger, playful dog. At a recent puppy social, she picked out the biggest puppy for a play buddy; an hour of hard play barely wore her out. 
She is starting to herd and will need to learn not to herd people as she would herd sheep.

She is four months old and has had her first round of vaccines, including rabies. She will get the second round on Feb. 15.

The ideal adopter will be eager to enroll Paiton in puppy class and will lose no time in introducing her to the big wide world.  She is still in the “socialization period,” and she is growing up fast.  Paiton will thrive with an owner who takes her education seriously and is committed to positive dog training methods. If you’re ready for some excitement and affection in your life, Paiton may be your dog!

Paiton’s adoption fee includes spay/neuter, basic vaccinations, rabies vaccination, and heartworm tested negative.

You can find her application here:

https://forms.gle/5eSBjHrWv7pTEEzUA

Questions? Contact us at connellpetrescue@gmail.com 

Thank you! And Paiton thanks you!

I was found the next morning by the 'office dog'. I am estimated to be 15 years old & I have both vision & hearing issues (Okay my hearing may actually be more selective than anything but I'll never tell). I am a VERY opinionated lady & will bark to let you know when I want you for something (to feed me or put me into the bed especially). I do have chronic dry eye & require daily medication for that. I have had a complete dental & have no teeth (only had 1 to begin with). My vet checked my heart & lungs and said they are both great. I am housetrained & I prefer to sleep with you in the bed. I like the other dogs & don't mind the cats. I however am not sure what I think about kids so the rescue recommends that there are no children in my forever home. I am spayed, HW-, UTD on all my shots, current on deworming & flea medication & regularly groomed. All I need is my very own home.Steps for adoption:Submit pre-adoption application found on our website (www.lostfantasystables.org)Application is reviewed & references contactedHome visit (by Zoom or in person)Meet & GreetSign adoption contract

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Forever Home Wanted: Meet Daphne!!

Daphne was recently rescued as a stray from a local shelter. Daphne is sweet girl that gets along well with people, kids and other dogs, but prefers not to live with Bossy dogs. Daphne is doing great in her foster home. Loves her walks, her people, children and calm dog siblings. Daphne appears to be house trained and leash trained and is learning more skills every day. Daphne needs entropion surgery on her eyes as her eyelashes grow the wrong way and irritate her eyes. This surgery is covered by the rescue and is a rather common surgery for dogs. If you think Daphne might be the right dog for your family, Email dogs@labradorsandfriends.org or fill out our online application at www.labradorsandfriends.org Daphne is located in Southern California.

animal.description:
It doesn't get much cuter than this tiny girl! Martha is a 1.5 year old spayed female chihuahua mix who weighs 9 lbs. This pretty lady was rescued from a high kill shelter after her elderly owner was no longer able to care for her. Martha is a total sweetheart!! She's very affectionate and wants nothing more than a warm lap where she can spend most of her day. Martha has a happy-go-lucky personality and makes friends with everyone she meets! She loves to be with her people and is happiest when she's snuggled up in bed or cuddling on the couch. Martha has been good with other dogs and didn't seem to mind the cats she met! She is very well mannered and even seems to be housebroken. We just love this adorable girl and know she will make a wonderful companion for the person willing to give her the time and attention she deserves! Please help us find Martha the amazing forever home she's been dreaming of! 

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/
We are a foster based organization, so we do not have a facility to visit. Please read our FAQs to learn more: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/faq

animal.description: Ever owned a dog named kitty? Well, now is your chance! Kitty is a big boy looking for a specific home, and will need a dog savvy and patient owner. Kitty has taken awhile to trust us here, but he has come a long way. Kitty is still unsure with overhandling, so he will need a hands off approach until he is totally comfortable in a new home. Because of his nervousness, and trust issues, he needs to go into a home with no children under 17 years of age. Due to his size and breed, he cannot live in an apartment or condo setting. He would LOVE a back yard where he can run and play! Kitty enjoys being the center of attention and would do best in a home with no other pets. He may get along with another dog, as long as it is a female. if you have a female dog at home, he would need to meet her prior to adoption to see if they want to be friends. Kitty really is a good boy, he just needs a chance. If you are willing to give him the time he needs to feel fully confident, we hope you will adopt him today!

animal.description:
Hi I'm WT! I'm one of the 29 pups from the Toccoa rescue, so I had a rough upbringing. I'm learning how wonderful it is to be with people in a nice home with lots of love. In new, uncertain situations, I tend to shut down/hide/cower if I don't know what's going on-like meeting new people who make me nervous. I've settled nicely into my foster home, and my foster Mom says I am a sweet, gentle, obedient lovable guy who is eager to please! I'm housebroken and have great leash manners. I have the softest, speckled ears and loving having them scratched and my neck rubbed. I'll ask for more petting by nosing my head into your lap for cuddling and will follow you around all day--just in case you need me for anything! . I'm a quiet guy who would prefer a quiet, calm home where I can chill out during the day. I'll be the kindest and most rewarding addition to a home that's willing to be patient with me while I learn the routines. If you are looking for a sweet and calm companion to share your home, I want to meet you. I'll be watching for you!
 Love, WT

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Elsie! I'm a petite lil pup who's very shy. My friends here at Atlanta Humane have been taking things slow with me day by day. Most things startle me, and since I'm still young, I'm adjusting to the world. I need a human who can love me and build my confidence up in a consistent and patient manner. I qualify for Foster First, which means you can foster me for 14 days prior to adoption to ensure I'm the perfect fit for your family!

animal.description: Hi, my name is Selah! I love to be petted and will definitely ask for more petting! I'm always on the go and enjoy lots of exercise, playing and maybe a little training would be good. I don't have much known history with dogs, cats, or kids, but would love to meet your current dog or children to see if we'd get along! I love to meet new people and get excited--sometimes I jump up on them to let them know how glad I am to meet them. That's one thing we could work on together. I'll be you've never seen a "wiggler" like me. My vet says I'm one of the most wiggle animals she's seen--that's because I'm a happy girl. My foster Mom says I'm very sweet and smart, and belly rubs are my favorite. Even if I'm in the middle of a nice walk and I meet a new friend, I will flop on my back and offer up my belly for that loving rub! That's my secret to getting new people to like me right away. If you are looking for a lovebug (a big one!), please come meet me. I'll be watching for you. Love, Selah!

animal.description:
Located outside of Atlanta, GA: **Bella baby is looking for a forever home to live out her golden years!** She might be 7-8 years old, but she is still full of life and full of love. She prefers spending her days lounging around, sun bathing, sleeping-in and being covered by her blankies (she hates being cold!). While she’s still learning how to play, she does enjoy running in the backyard with her foster mom.

She is the epitome of a gentle giant and rarely barks. In typical Dane fashion, she is a leaner and prefers being with her people and to be loved. She is not a fan of being left alone, but is not destructive. She would do best in a home with owners who are home more often than not. She would also do best in a home without young children (she startles if woken suddenly). 

She has other dog and cat foster siblings and has done very well with them. If they get too close to her food, she will give a warning growl, but hey, we don’t like people getting close to our food either. The only time she shows interest in cats is if they’re running in the yard; other than that, you can find Bella curled up next to them. She does well on a leash and will signal when she needs to go potty. 

Since Bella is considered a senior (despite how she feels mentally), she does have certain age related needs that will be considered when placing her in a forever home. Her blood work looked phenomenal despite being underweight. She has gained a few pounds since coming to us, but could stand to gain a few more even though she will always need to be kept lean. She can be a picky eater in the morning, but seems to get her appetite throughout the day. 

X-rays showed spondylosis (spine) and arthritis of the hips. The vet thinks this is normal aging and there isn’t much more she would recommend beyond supplements. She is a bit wobbly on her feet so she will need a home with extremely limited stairs. Rugs and carpets are her best friend, but we bought her some booties to help on hard wood. 

Bella is an absolute sweetheart and anyone would be lucky to welcome this mature lady into their lives. She is spayed, UTD on vaccines, prevention and heartworm negative.

To fill out an application, please review our FAQ on our website FIRST before filling out an application at www.risingabovegdf.org/

**If you do not meet our requirements, your application will not be processed. Please read the FAQ first.**

animal.description:
Bolt is a 2 year old Retriever mix who is looking for a new leash on life! He was brought to the shelter by his previous owners, who's schedule didn't allow them enough time to work with him, but he also wasn't getting along with the cats in the home. Bolt is a very loving, playful, active, and protective fellow, and would be best in a home with experienced dog owners. While he was great with the kids in his previous home, he could get protective over them when friends would come over, so we recommend a home where there won't be lots of new people coming and going. Bolt has shown to have a high prey-drive, and should be the only animal in the home. He was used to being crated in the home when alone and loves going on walks. Bolt has shown severe food aggression, so we would recommend feeding him in a crate or room where he can be alone until he is done eating. He knows some basic commands, and will work for treats! Bolt knows there is the right home out there, and can't wait to show off for you. Once this beautiful boy knows you, you'll get to see just how sweet and goofy he is at heart! Bolt is neutered, current on his vaccinations, heartworm negative, and microchipped. All he needs now is you! He is available for adoption at the Benbrook Waggin' Tails Adoption Center, open every day from 12-6 pm by appointment!

Call us today at 817-249-3647 to schedule an appointment to meet Bolt!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Foster or Forever Home Wanted: Meet Bradley aka Bentley!

Sometimes it is all about being in the right place at the right time. The first two pictures of Bradley laying down was how he actually began his journey into the LAF family. You see, Bradley, who had no name at the time, was lost and happened upon a bed and some water at a camp ground. As luck would have it, the site he found belonged to one of our amazing volunteers! This sweet, skinny boy found a warm spot to lay his tired, beaten up body. To ensure no one lost him at the camp site prior we had our volunteer surrender him to the Friends of Lake Elsinore Shelter, put her name down for adoption/finder, and we had him wait his mandatory stray hold. Sadly, no one came for him, so we immediately got him out of the shelter and to our vet. Bradley had a lump on his neck that was hard and concerning, we had it removed while he was being neutered and sent it out for pathology. We are still waiting for the report to come back and we are hoping it is nothing serious. Bradley is a kind, gentle boy who loves everyone. He just wants to be loved and we really want to get him into a loving home ASAP!

If you would like to help donate towards Bradley's medical care you can do so via:

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Finnley. I'm a pit mix, 2 years old, 50 lbs, & I have a white & black spotted coloring.

I'm basically just a wiggly little porkchop of a dog. I'm always waggin' my tail so hard my whole body moves, I dart around at super mega lightning speed like you couldn't even imagine, & I'm always on the GO GO GO!!! I'm always playing any chance I get, & any time I'm not, I'm cuddlin' up right into your lap & up in your face. I LOVE toys, especially tennis balls! It might stem from me trying to replace the ones of my own that I lost? Maybe, but what's done is done I guess! I might love them a little TOO much, honestly. They usually don't last more than 10 minutes or so before they're in pieces! I'm kind of a rascal like that. I guess you could say I'm like half dog, half pig. I'm all short & stocky & I snort like one, for sure! & I've got the colors of a cow? Like what the HECK am I!? Sorry for the foul language there. Having a bit of an existential crisis here! Anyway, what was I talking about? I forgot...hmm...
Oh, hi there! My name is Finnley! What? We already went over that part? Never mind, sorry! I just got lost in the beautiful eyes of yours. Anyway, come take me home, why don't ya!? I know you're dyin' to have a little stud man like me around!

I'm up to date on shots, neutered, chipped, & ready to go! I also tested negative for heartworm. If you're looking for a stocky, stubby guy to add to your family, come check me out sometime!

animal.description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Jules is an adorable 3-month-old Terrier blend. He has a sweet temperament and is active and playful. He will make a loyal companion.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his puppy cuteness wears off.
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Like most puppies, he may chew on anything within his reach to include but not limited to baseboards, shoes, socks, children's toys, electrical cords, plants, etc.
His adoption fee is $250. This includes his neuter surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccinations, Bravecto, Drontal Plus, Tri-Heart Plus Chewable Tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Fill out an Adoption Application
Lucy is a 135lbs of Love and suits her name Lovable Lucy. While Lucy loves men if they are on the couch with her, she is timid and skittish around men when they are standing and moving about however, she is not aggressive just scared.
The best home for her will be one with a woman/women who will love her and in a family situation will need a man who has a lot of love and patience. He would need to understand and be willing to work with her to gain her trust. Here in her foster home she loves to cuddle on the couch with her foster Dad and after a few weeks he is now worth trusting for a great breakfast.
Lucy will need work on walking on a leash so a home with a fenced in yard, no cats, and lots of love for this beauty is the best for Lucy.
With her foster Mom she is a buddy and follows her around, gives gentle kisses and ear nibbles and loves to be loved. Lucy also loves the other dogs and plays with the small and big ones alike. She has met the grandkids at her foster home and she is fine.
If you are a true dog lover and lover of the breed and you will make Lucy your focus and not expect her to hurry up and love everyone then you will be the right forever home for her. She needs loving hands and some positive reinforcement training for walking. Lucy is not crate trained but she is fully house trained and has not had one single accident in her foster home.
Lucy is being fostered in Walnutport, PA.Application Fees, Adoption Donations and Rescue Policy: Please know that 100% of our funds are used for rescuing the dogs.
Our rescue policy requires the following:

Adopters must have their primary residence in one of the following states: Pennsylvania, Ohio, New Jersey, Delaware, Maryland, West Virginia, Virginia, and parts of North Carolina and parts of New York.
We will not adopt a giant breed dog to homes where the dog will have access to highly varnished hardwood steps inside the home. Any inside steps to which the dog(s) have access, must have carpeting, securely fixed stair treads, or a non-skid surface. We encourage you to remediate potential safety issues while your application is under review, prior to the home visit.
Methods or devices using pain or force on the dog to control the dog, or to deter undesirable behavior is prohibited.
Applications for giant breed dogs must be submitted by the property owner.
Homes with children under 6 years of age will not be approved for adoption.
Homes with children should have a fenced yard.
Pets currently in the applicant's home must have a history of appropriate veterinary care. Veterinary records will be checked.
All references must be checked before any visitation of the dog is permitted at the foster home.
All family members must be present during the home visit to the applicant's home.
Any dog(s) in the applicant's home must have an introductory meeting with the rescue dog being considered, before any adoption can be completed.
Homes with intact dogs will not be approved for adoption. Exceptions to this policy can be found on the Adoptable Dog Page.

For additional information please review our FAQs or contact mastiffstomutts@gmail.com
Mastiffs To Mutts Rescue reserves the right to approve or deny any adoption that occurs through this organization without disclosure. We reserve the right to make exceptions for special circumstances.

Tyson is a Carolina Dog or Yellow Lab or mix, best guess.  He is about 3yrs young and 65-70lbs. 

 

He was found tied to a tree at a construction site.  He had been there for many days, the construction crew was setting out food and water for him.  A person got him safe into boarding, however, he remained there for many months, until he was abandoned.  He is now in a foster home.   

 

Tyson is a sweet boy who loves loves loves to play catch.  He is very good with people and hangs out well with other dogs.  He should not be in a home with cats, though.  He is kennel trained, hangs out in his kennel all day just fine.  He does amazing on walks – when the leash is tugged, he stops and sits (learned this in his previous life).  Tyson is a big boy with lots of love to give. 

 

His adoption fee is $200.  For more info about Tyson, contact his foster Sharon at sharon.c.epstein@gmail.com

 

Thank you for considering a rescue dog!

Squeaky ones are the BEST! She loves to shred them too…lol. Tennis Balls? Yes please, Panera loves play time! You’ll fall in love with her big beautiful brown eyes that pierce into yours. She is an indoor dog, she goes out to potty when asked “Want to go outside”? She will also sit by the door to let you know it’s time to go out. She loves to patrol around the back yard, so a home with a securely fenced yard is a MUST! She needs a new loving home because sadly her owner just passed away. She was his protector and best friend. She was used to being by his side 24/7 and she needs a new owner that will be with her most of the time. Her ideal home is as an ONLY DOG! No cats, she will chase them and no small children, as she isn’t used to them. Due to breed and size restrictions in rental property, homeowners only need apply! Breed savvy is a PLUS. She is spayed, microchipped and up to date on vaccinations. She is an inside the house only dog with outside potty and play privileges. Are you ready to have this sweet girl by your side? OFFICE
If you are interested in this dog or would like more information Please scroll down to the “MORE ABOUT US” button Click that . Then click on the adoption link and fill out the application.

animal.description:
Hank is one of our all time favorite pups! He is an 8 year old Boxer/Pit who often acts like he is a puppy! He has the perfect balance of playful and mellow! He loves toys, food, and cuddles. Hank has bursts of energy where he loves to run and play and then he is happy to curl up and sleep in his bed. He is known to sleep in in the morning and often snores, so beware!

 Hank gets along with everyone (dogs, cats, kids, men, women). He doesn't realize his size and thinks he is a lap dog so he will sometimes crawl in your lap for cuddles. 

Hank is housebroken and crate trained although we never crate him because he is so well behaved. He never has accidents and doesn't chew on anything. He does well on leash and enjoys car rides! He also knows sit and shake! 

Hank is up to date on vaccines, microchipped and neutered. He is a little hard of hearing but otherwise in great health. He just had bloodwork done which came back normal and had a dental so he is ready to go for awhile. 

If you'd like to meet this awesome dude, submit an application on our website at www.dominoeffectanimalrescue.org

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Tiara! I'm a 3 year old female beauty. They say I'm one of the sweetest, most loving German Shepherds you'll ever meet... to my people! I need slow introductions to new people though and to keep socializing. I'm thankful that MDRN got me out of the shelter where my former family left me, and have given me this 2nd chance. I'm crate trained and housebroken. I'm a great watchdog and I love attention. I also love food. I can only have a certain kind or my stomach hurts... So even though I want everything, I can only have my food and pancreatic enzymes to go with it due to my pancreatic insufficiency (EPI). I wait by the door until my foster mama gets home. Like most GSDs, I'm pretty loyal to my person. I do not mind the cats or the other dogs. The kids are great and take me outside to play with me. Although I will miss my foster family briefly, I will quickly bond with a new fam. I'm spayed, fully vetted and vaccinated, microchipped, and ready for my forever family!!!
To help pay for vet bills and care (transportation, food, toys, etc..) a $300 donation is requested at the time of adoption. All of our adoptions are contingent upon an approved application, home visit, reference check, obedience training agreement, and signing of adoption contract. All our dogs are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, and microchipped before adoption. Our dogs are companion animals that live indoors as part of your family. Please do not apply if your plan is to have them as outside dogs, garage dogs, porch dogs or outside kennel dogs. We do not ship dogs. All of our dogs are in private foster homes. We are not a shelter with hours. A visit can be arranaged after an adoption questionnaire has been filled out and sent in. Please try email first. We are all volunteers that work so we can not easily take or make phone calls.

animal.description:
Lilabelle is an 18 month old female Dalmatian / Bulldog that came to us when her babies were given away much too early and she needed a place to call home.  She was able to raise her last two babies and then 6 orphaned puppies needed her.  The puppies lost their mother when they were 2 1/2 weeks old and needed a surrogate.  Lilabelle immediately took to them and was able to nurse them until they were old enough to be on their own.  Lilabelle has the sweetest personality and loves people and kids. She loves attention and will always be your best friend.  She does fine with the other dogs here and occasionally has to be reminded that the cats don't want to be her playmate.  Lilabelle weighs 48 lbs.

If you would like an application go to our website (https://humanesocietypc.com/) and download one and email it back as a Word or PDF document. Please no Google documents.

This dog's adoption fee is $190. That fee includes spaying/ neutering, microchipping, deworming and vaccinations.

animal.description: Hi I'm Ruby. I'm a social butterfly that can't get enough of everyone and everything! Do you have parties? The more, the merrier! Love to go for long walks on the beach or hiking mountains? I'm the pup for you! Ok, so we don't have many beaches or any mountains nearby, but the point is I want to be with you every step of the way! I need to meet any children and dogs in the home to make sure it's a perfect match. Ruby will be shown by appointment only. If you are interested in learning more about this animal, please fill out an application by clicking here . Be sure to include Ruby 1370363 when filling out the survey. After reviewing your application, we will only be reaching out to you if the animal is a good fit for your home.

animal.description: Hi, my name is GWEN and I would love to meet you. I am a Spayed Female Pit Bull Terrier. The shelter staff think I am about 2 years and 6 months old. I have been at the shelter since Jan 20, 2021. Meet Gwen! This little wiggle-butt came to the shelter as a stray so shelter staff and volunteers are still getting to know her. Personality: Gwen is a people pibble who loves to make new friends! She is ready to make a home in your heart and on your couch! History: Her history with other dogs, cats, and small animals is unknown, however, she has shown some reactivity while here. We always recommend slow and careful introductions! Energy levels: Gwen is a young girl is sweet as pie, with a good amount of energy, but is dealing with a bit of a medical issue, due to a Luxating Patellas (3 out of 4). Ideal home: Gwen would prefer a home with minimal stairs, as her knee does cause some discomfort. Family: She needs a family that is looking for a lovebug! Children in the home should be old enough to respect her space and understand her medical needs. Is there no doubt, she`s the one for you? Come down and meet her today!
animal.name: GWEN

animal.description: 1156770 Lana is a 4-year-old, 88-pound, spayed female, bully breed mix-type dog. This energetic girl will pull on the leash with excitement and enjoys going for walks. She is initially shy when you approach her but she warms up to you quickly. She seems receptive to meeting other dogs and a meet and greet is recommended if you have another dog at home. She has been to the dog parks but we don't recommend you take her to one until you are familiar with each other. She has lived with other dogs and children and is reported to be housebroken to a doggie door. Lana came in with 1156771 Archer as a surrender due to owner becoming homeless.

animal.description: Ginger was surrendered to the shelter with her friend Nausi. Ginger has been pretty shy here at the shelter but might just need some extra time to warm up to her new people. Her previous owner stated that she's very outgoing, friendly, and affectionate! She has spent her time both living indoors and outdoors. She is said to be skijor and mushing trained! Ginger would benefit from a basic obedience class to learn how to be a proper lady in society as she still needs to learn basic commands like sit. She will also need work on being housebroken! Ginger is a young girl who just needs someone to put a little extra love, time, and training into her! Ginger is said to do well with other dogs but we do not know how she does with cats, pocket pets, and livestock. Being that she is an Alaskan Husky and they have a higher prey drive it might be best for her to go to a home without smaller pets. If you are wanting to try and introduce her to them just make sure to do it in a safe and controlled environment. If this girl looks like the pup you've been waiting for to make your family complete please give the shelter a call!
animal.name: GINGER
